  AND THE APOCALYPSE

00:01:48.942 --> 00:01:52.012
MEET TO DANCE A DIRTY TANGO.

00:01:52.079 --> 00:01:54.081
IT'S A SPECIAL PLACE,

00:01:54.147 --> 00:01:56.750
A BIT CLOSER
 THAN YOU MIGHT THINK,

00:01:56.817 --> 00:01:59.686
THAT DRAWS A UNIQUE GROUP
 OF OUTSIDERS,

00:01:59.753 --> 00:02:02.322
LOOKING FOR
  AN AWFULLY BEAUTIFUL LIFE,

00:02:02.389 --> 00:02:06.093
ON THE EDGE OF
 A BEAUTIFULLY AWFUL PARADISE.

00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:08.528
UH, YOU KNOW WHAT,

00:02:08.595 --> 00:02:12.265
THERE'S VERY FEW PEOPLE THAT
 KNOW ABOUT THE SALTON SEA...

00:02:12.332 --> 00:02:13.934
VERY FEW.

00:02:14.001 --> 00:02:15.102
Les Marty:
  IF THEY DON'T KNOW
 WHERE IT'S AT,

00:02:15.168 --> 00:02:18.105
YOU TELL 'EM 50 MILES
SOUTH OF PALM SPRINGS--

00:02:18.171 --> 00:02:19.806
WHICH I USE
 AS A REFERENCE POINT.

00:02:24.211 --> 00:02:27.414
CALIFORNIA'S VERSION
OF THE FRENCH RIVIERA,

00:02:27.481 --> 00:02:29.650
WITH BEAUTIFUL WEATHER,

00:02:29.716 --> 00:02:31.551
WATER AVAILABLE FOR BOATING,

00:02:31.618 --> 00:02:34.621
AND AS A PLACE FOR RECREATION
 AND FISHING AND SO ON.

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:40.627
THE FISHING IN THE SUMMER
 IS GREAT...GREAT!

00:02:40.694 --> 00:02:43.864
THE HOTTER THE WATER,
  THE BETTER THE FISHING.

00:02:43.930 --> 00:02:45.465
THAT'S NOT EDIBLE FISH.

00:02:45.532 --> 00:02:48.235
IF THEY ARE EATING THOSE FISH,
AND THEY EAT VERY MUCH OF 'EM,

00:02:48.301 --> 00:02:50.537
THEY'LL GET
  BOTULISM POISONING.

00:02:50.604 --> 00:02:52.773
THAT SEA IS FILTHY.

00:02:52.839 --> 00:02:56.309
DEAD FISH, DEAD BIRDS,
 DEAD EVERYTHING OVER THERE.

00:02:56.376 --> 00:02:57.678
WE HAVE THE ODOR PROBLEM,

00:02:57.744 --> 00:02:59.780
WE HAVE
  THE INSECT PROBLEM--

00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:02.349
NAMELY THE COMMON HOUSEFLY.

00:03:02.416 --> 00:03:03.450
IT GETS HOT HERE
IN THE SUMMER.

00:03:03.517 --> 00:03:04.885
IT'S 120 DEGREES HERE,

00:03:04.951 --> 00:03:07.721
100 DEGREES AT MIDNIGHT;
 YOU KNOW, IT'S WARM.

00:03:07.788 --> 00:03:10.090
BUT THAT'S WHAT WE GOT
 AIR CONDITIONING FOR.

00:03:11.658 --> 00:03:13.994
WE DO EVEN GO SWIMMING
 IN THE WATER.

00:03:14.061 --> 00:03:16.630
IT'S MORE SALTIER
THAN THE OCEAN.

00:03:16.697 --> 00:03:18.765
AND IT HEALS YOUR SKIN.

00:03:18.832 --> 00:03:22.836
IF YOU HAVE A SKIN PROBLEM,
  IT HEALS YOUR SKIN.

00:03:22.903 --> 00:03:26.540
WHY CLEAN UP
 A MOST USEFUL SEWER?

00:03:26.606 --> 00:03:28.809
IT'S THE GREATEST SEWER
  THE WORLD HAS EVER SEEN.

00:03:28.875 --> 00:03:29.910
LEAVE IT THAT WAY.

00:03:29.976 --> 00:03:32.279
IT'S PERFECT FOR THAT PURPOSE.

00:03:32.345 --> 00:03:34.347
IF IT HAD BEEN
 HANDLED CORRECTLY,

00:03:34.414 --> 00:03:38.018
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN ANOTHER
PALM SPRINGS RIGHT NOW.

00:03:41.121 --> 00:03:42.089
THE SMELL.

00:03:44.558 --> 00:03:47.327
IT'S THE SMELL--A LOT.

00:03:47.394 --> 00:03:50.197
AND THEN THE FACT THAT WE
 DON'T HAVE ANYTHING HERE.

00:03:50.263 --> 00:03:51.998
IT IS RATHER BLEAK.

00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:54.634
BLEAK IS THE WORD.

00:03:54.701 --> 00:03:56.837
THE MOST BEAUTIFUL BODY
OF WATER IN CALIFORNIA.

00:03:56.903 --> 00:03:58.872
YOU CAN GO BOATING,
 YOU CAN GO FISHING,

00:03:58.939 --> 00:04:00.173
YOU CAN GO JET SKIING.

00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:02.109
YOU HAVE BEAUTIFUL
 ROCK FORMATIONS.

00:04:02.175 --> 00:04:03.376
YOU HAVE THE MOUNTAINS,

00:04:03.443 --> 00:04:04.945
WHERE YOU CAN SEE,
 IN THE SUMMERTIME,

00:04:05.011 --> 00:04:07.347
YOU CAN SEE SNOWCAPS
 ON THE MOUNTAINS.

00:04:07.414 --> 00:04:09.015
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING.

00:04:09.082 --> 00:04:11.318
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING THAT
 YOU CAN FIND NOWHERE ELSE.

00:04:11.384 --> 00:04:13.587
THERE'S NO FAST FOODS HERE.

00:04:13.653 --> 00:04:15.589
THERE'S NO RECREATION

00:04:15.655 --> 00:04:18.625
FOR YOUNGSTERS,
  KIDS OR ANYTHING.

00:04:18.692 --> 00:04:20.160
I MEAN THERE AIN'T NOTHING HERE.

00:04:20.227 --> 00:04:22.896
YOU CAN'T GET NOTHING--
 THE STORES CLOSE AT 6:00!

00:04:22.963 --> 00:04:26.266
SO YOU CAN'T BUY BOOZE
 AFTER 6:00.

00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:27.367
I LIKE IT HERE.

00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:29.069
I'LL DIE HERE.

00:04:29.136 --> 00:04:30.470
I MEAN, COME ON,

00:04:30.537 --> 00:04:31.438
WE AIN'T EVEN GOT A MALL
 OR NOTHIN' OUT HERE.

00:04:31.505 --> 00:04:33.306
WE'RE AWAY FROM EVERYTHING!

00:04:33.373 --> 00:04:37.944
BUT IT IS JUST A SUPER,
SUPER, WONDERFUL PLACE!

00:04:44.084 --> 00:04:47.020
(* Rock Music )

00:05:12.412 --> 00:05:14.247
John Waters:
  LYING WELL BELOW SEA LEVEL,

00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:18.051
IN ONE OF THE HOTTEST
  AND DRIEST VALLEYS ON EARTH,

00:05:18.118 --> 00:05:23.523
SITS THE WONDERFULLY
  BIZARRE SALTON SEA.

00:05:23.590 --> 00:05:26.193
IT WAS ONCE HAILED AS THE
  FISHING CAPITAL OF THE WORLD

00:05:26.259 --> 00:05:29.462
AND EVEN RIVALED THE NEARBY
  RESORT TOWN OF PALM SPRINGS

00:05:29.529 --> 00:05:30.864
IN POPULARITY.

00:05:32.966 --> 00:05:35.368
BUT NOW AFTER
  A STRING OF CATASTROPHES,

00:05:35.435 --> 00:05:39.639
IT SITS VIRTUALLY
  ABANDONED AND FORGOTTEN.

00:05:39.706 --> 00:05:42.242
ONLY A HANDFUL
 OF ECCENTRICS REMAIN,

00:05:42.309 --> 00:05:45.011
CARVING OUT THEIR OWN
  SLICE OF PARADISE,

00:05:45.078 --> 00:05:49.549
ON THE SHORES OF THIS SO-CALLED
 "ECOLOGICAL DISASTER."

00:05:49.616 --> 00:05:53.253
BUT DISASTER IS WELL KNOWN TO
 THE PEOPLE OF IMPERIAL VALLEY.

00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:59.226
IN FACT, THE SALTON SEA ITSELF
  IS JUST ONE BIG MISTAKE.

00:06:01.995 --> 00:06:03.597
IN 1901,

00:06:03.663 --> 00:06:06.733
DEVELOPERS WITH A DREAM
  TO TRANSFORM THE DESERT,

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:08.802
DIVERTED WATER
  FROM THE COLORADO RIVER

00:06:08.869 --> 00:06:13.807
TO A DRIED LAKE BED
 NAMED THE SALTON SINK.

00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:16.676
AS AN ANCIENT OVERFLOW
  FOR THE COLORADO RIVER,

00:06:16.743 --> 00:06:18.645
THE SOIL WAS NUTRIENT-RICH

00:06:18.712 --> 00:06:20.180
AND THE WARM CLIMATE

00:06:20.247 --> 00:06:23.617
MADE IT POSSIBLE
  TO GROW CROPS YEAR-ROUND.

00:06:23.683 --> 00:06:27.354
RENAMED THE IMPERIAL VALLEY,
 LAND WAS SOLD,

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:31.224
AND FARMING FLOURISHED
 IN THE DESERT.

00:06:31.291 --> 00:06:33.493
HOWEVER,
  SILT EVENTUALLY BLOCKED

00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:35.362
THE ENTRANCE TO THE CANAL,

00:06:35.428 --> 00:06:39.065
AND WATER DELIVERY WAS
 ALL BUT CUT OFF TO THE FARMERS.

00:06:39.132 --> 00:06:41.768
UNDER PRESSURE FROM
  DESPERATE INVESTORS,

00:06:41.835 --> 00:06:44.804
ENGINEERS MADE SEVERAL
  UNPROTECTED CUTS

00:06:44.871 --> 00:06:47.007
INTO THE RIVER.

00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:51.111
THEN IN 1905,
  AMIDST HEAVY SPRING RAINS,

00:06:51.177 --> 00:06:54.347
THE ERRATIC COLORADO
  BROKE FREE, CHANGED COURSE,

00:06:54.414 --> 00:06:57.651
AND HEADED STRAIGHT
  FOR THE IMPERIAL VALLEY.

00:06:57.717 --> 00:06:59.653
THE RIVER THAT HAD ONCE
  BROUGHT PROSPERITY,

00:06:59.719 --> 00:07:02.689
NOW BEGAN TO DESTROY
  EVERYTHING IN ITS PATH,

00:07:02.756 --> 00:07:06.192
AS IT BEGAN TO COLLECT
  IN THE LOWEST POINT,

00:07:06.259 --> 00:07:08.528
THE SALTON SINK.

00:07:10.463 --> 00:07:13.266
IN ORDER TO PROTECT
  A VITAL SHIPPING ROUTE,

00:07:13.333 --> 00:07:16.303
SOUTHERN PACIFIC RAILROAD
  TYCOON, EDWARD HARRIMAN,

00:07:16.369 --> 00:07:19.539
INTERVENED WITH THE SUPPORT OF
 PRESIDENT THEODORE ROOSEVELT,

00:07:19.606 --> 00:07:22.409
TO DO BATTLE WITH THE RIVER.

00:07:22.475 --> 00:07:23.777
WITH THOUSANDS OF MEN,

00:07:23.843 --> 00:07:26.079
AND COUNTLESS TONS
  OF ROCK AND SAND,

00:07:26.146 --> 00:07:28.315
THE RAILROAD AND
  THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT

00:07:28.381 --> 00:07:31.384
ATTEMPTED SEVERAL TIMES
  TO PLUG THE BREACH.

00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:34.955
AFTER TREMENDOUS EFFORT
  AND 16 MONTHS OF FLOODING,

00:07:35.021 --> 00:07:38.124
THEY FINALLY MANAGED
  TO TURN BACK THE RIVER.

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:42.762
THE DESERT HEAT
 SHOULD HAVE QUICKLY EVAPORATED

00:07:42.829 --> 00:07:44.597
THIS MAN-MADE MISTAKE.

00:07:44.664 --> 00:07:47.400
HOWEVER,
  SALTY IRRIGATION RUNOFF

00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:49.369
FROM FARMERS
  IN THE IMPERIAL VALLEY,

00:07:49.436 --> 00:07:51.671
SUSTAINED THE NEWLY-FORMED SEA,

00:07:51.738 --> 00:07:55.742
AND INCREASED ITS SALINITY
 TO NEAR OCEAN LEVELS.

00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:59.779
AN ENGINEERING SCREW-UP
  HAD GIVEN BIRTH TO A SEA

00:07:59.846 --> 00:08:04.584
35 MILES LONG
  AND 15 MILES WIDE

00:08:04.651 --> 00:08:07.020
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE DESERT.

00:08:12.559 --> 00:08:14.394
(* Music )

00:08:25.805 --> 00:08:27.007
Harold Gaston:
  AND THEY THOUGHT

00:08:27.073 --> 00:08:30.143
THAT THE SALTON SEA
WOULD BE GOOD FOR FISH,

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:32.712
IF THEY COULD GET THE RIGHT
KIND OF FISH TO GROW IN THERE.

00:08:32.779 --> 00:08:35.915
SO THEY WENT DOWN TO SAN FELIPE
  AND SEEN--

00:08:35.982 --> 00:08:38.918
FISH OUT OF THE SURF THERE.

00:08:38.985 --> 00:08:41.454
BUT THEY TRIED TO KEEP ALL
 OF THE SHARKS OUT OF THERE,

00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:43.523
THEY DIDN'T WANT TO PUT
 ANY SHARKS IN HERE.

00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:44.858
AND THEY BROUGHT THE FISH UP--

00:08:44.924 --> 00:08:47.127
I MEET THEM AT SALT CREEK
 UP HERE--

00:08:47.193 --> 00:08:49.763
AND THEY PUT THE FISH IN
  RIGHT THERE AT SALT CREEK.

00:08:49.829 --> 00:08:53.466
THAT WAS 1951, IN JUNE.

00:08:53.533 --> 00:08:56.770
FINALLY IN 1957, WE STARTED
CATCHING A FEW CORVINA

00:08:56.836 --> 00:08:58.071
AT SALT CREEK.

00:08:58.138 --> 00:08:59.339
WE CAUGHT
  THE FIRST TWO LIMITS OF FISH

00:08:59.406 --> 00:09:01.141
THAT WERE EVER CAUGHT
  IN THE SALTON SEA.

00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:02.609
WE CAUGHT 12 FISH THERE,

00:09:02.675 --> 00:09:05.311
AVERAGED
  BETWEEN 8 AND 10 POUNDS.

00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:07.847
AND THAT STARTED
THE FISHING DOWN HERE.

00:09:07.914 --> 00:09:11.618
BY 1960 THERE WERE EIGHT
 BOAT LANDINGS AROUND THE SEA,

00:09:11.684 --> 00:09:14.654
LAUNCHING 50 TO 100 BOATS
 A DAY.

00:09:16.723 --> 00:09:19.359
THEY WERE HERE BY THE HUNDREDS,
 ALL UP AND DOWN THIS HIGHWAY,

00:09:19.426 --> 00:09:22.662
AND WE FED
 100 FISHERMAN A DAY HERE

00:09:22.729 --> 00:09:24.798
DURING THE SUMMERTIME,
 YOU KNOW.

00:09:24.864 --> 00:09:26.399
Male Narrator:
  IF YOU LIKE TO FISH,

00:09:26.466 --> 00:09:28.768
THERE ARE PLENTY
  IN THE SALTON SEA.

00:09:28.835 --> 00:09:31.905
SO FAR THEY'VE BEEN
  CAUGHT UP TO 33 POUNDS.

00:09:31.971 --> 00:09:35.708
THERE ARE CORVINA, TORTUAVA
  AND MULLET IN ABUNDANCE.

00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:38.978
IT'S NOT ANYTHING
 LIKE IT USED TO BE,

00:09:39.045 --> 00:09:40.413
IT USED TO BE BEAUTIFUL!

00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:43.149
THERE USED TO BE JUST
  TRAILERS AND MOTOR HOMES

00:09:43.216 --> 00:09:49.656
AND SKIERS AND BOATERS
  AND SWIMMERS...EVERYWHERE!

00:09:49.722 --> 00:09:52.459
IN THE '60s, PARTICULARLY,

00:09:52.525 --> 00:09:54.861
IT WAS REALLY A VIBRANT SEA.

00:09:54.928 --> 00:09:58.064
YOU NOT ONLY HAD SKIING,
  SWIMMING AND SUCH,

00:09:58.131 --> 00:10:00.567
YOU HAD THE RICH FOLKS
 COMING DOWN FROM L.A.

00:10:00.633 --> 00:10:02.368
WITH THE SPORTFISHING BOATS,

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:04.204
PUTTING IN, I GUESS,
  PROBABLY IN NORTH SHORE,

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:07.574
AND DOING THE SPORTFISHING
  ON THE WEEKENDS.

00:10:07.640 --> 00:10:10.910
ALL KINDS OF NICE LITTLE,
 YOU KNOW, SECLUDED PLACES

00:10:10.977 --> 00:10:13.646
FOR THOSE WHO WANTED TO
 GET AWAY FROM THE CROWD.

00:10:13.713 --> 00:10:17.183
SWIMMING AND DRINKING BEER.

00:10:17.250 --> 00:10:19.486
( Laughs )

00:10:19.552 --> 00:10:22.689
DRINKING BEER AND THROWING--
  SKIMMING ROCKS.

00:10:22.755 --> 00:10:26.059
THE WATER WAS BRACKISH THEN,
 IT ISN'T LIKE TODAY.

00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:30.630
IT WAS LESS SALTY
 THAN THE OCEAN AT THAT TIME.

00:10:30.697 --> 00:10:32.899
WE USED TO HAVE FISH FRIES.

00:10:32.966 --> 00:10:35.001
SO ANYBODY THAT CAUGHT ANY
 BROUGHT 'EM UP

00:10:35.068 --> 00:10:40.273
AND THE CORVINA--
 AND, OH GOD, THEY WERE SO GOOD!

00:10:40.340 --> 00:10:43.076
THEY COOKED 'EM
 IN A BEER BATTER.

00:10:43.143 --> 00:10:45.044
FUN! FUN! FUN!

00:10:45.111 --> 00:10:46.379
Male Narrator:
  WATER MEANS FUN,

00:10:46.446 --> 00:10:49.415
AND SALTON SEA WATER IS IDEAL
 FOR THE AMATEUR SKIER,

00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:50.884
SUPERB FOR THE SKILLFUL.

00:10:50.950 --> 00:10:52.418
THE REASON?

00:10:52.485 --> 00:10:54.187
THE LOW ALTITUDE
  AND THE ACCOMPANYING DENSITY

00:10:54.254 --> 00:10:56.523
MAKES SALTON SEA ONE OF
  THE FASTEST BODIES OF WATER

00:10:56.589 --> 00:10:57.524
ON EARTH.

00:10:57.590 --> 00:10:59.425
IN THE '50s AND '60s,

00:10:59.492 --> 00:11:00.860
THE SEA TOOK IN MORE--

00:11:00.927 --> 00:11:04.898
HAD MORE TOURISTS
 THAN YOSEMITE PARK.

00:11:04.964 --> 00:11:07.200
DOWN HERE WE HAD BOAT RACES.

00:11:07.267 --> 00:11:09.469
WE HAD EVERYTHING.

00:11:09.536 --> 00:11:12.138
WE HAD ALL KINDS OF CELEBRITIES
 AT THE SALTON SEA

00:11:12.205 --> 00:11:13.940
AND BIG EVENTS.

00:11:14.007 --> 00:11:15.708
( Glass Shatters )

00:11:15.775 --> 00:11:17.911
WE HAD SONNY BONO.

00:11:17.977 --> 00:11:19.245
WE HAD THE MARX BROTHERS,

00:11:19.312 --> 00:11:21.714
AND THE BEACH BOYS
 USED TO COME OUT HERE.

00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:26.352
THE YACHT CLUBS ON ALL SIDES
  WERE DEVELOPING AND BOOMING

00:11:26.419 --> 00:11:28.421
AND BOATS WERE
  IN AND OUT OF THE WATER.

00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:31.157
EVENTUALLY THIS AREA

00:11:31.224 --> 00:11:35.828
WAS LAID OUT
  AS A RETIREMENT COMMUNITY.

00:11:35.895 --> 00:11:40.066
THEY BASICALLY LAID THIS OUT,
  PUT IN THE INFRASTRUCTURE,

00:11:40.133 --> 00:11:42.669
AND THEN STARTED SELLING IT.

00:11:42.735 --> 00:11:44.871
Male Narrator:
  OUT OF THE LABOR
  AND MIND OF MAN,

00:11:44.938 --> 00:11:46.306
OUT OF THE BARREN DESERT,

00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:47.941
OUT OF THE MANY MONTHS
  OF ENDEAVOR

00:11:48.007 --> 00:11:49.576
AND DARING IMAGINATION,

00:11:49.642 --> 00:11:50.977
A CITY IS BORN.

00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:53.213
AND BUSINESS SEES A FUTURE
 IN SALTON CITY

00:11:53.279 --> 00:11:55.882
AND BECOMES PART OF
  THE GREAT SCHEME OF THINGS.

00:11:55.949 --> 00:11:57.784
A MAJOR OIL COMPANY
  BECOMES A PART,

00:11:57.850 --> 00:11:59.786
A MODERN RESTAURANT.

00:11:59.852 --> 00:12:01.421
PEOPLE CAME ON BUSES--

00:12:01.487 --> 00:12:02.889
BUSLOADS OF PEOPLE--

00:12:02.956 --> 00:12:06.492
TO SPEND THE DAY
  AND BUY THE LOTS.

00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:08.361
FREE LITTLE TOURS
  OF THE PLACE

00:12:08.428 --> 00:12:13.766
AND THEY HAD LITTLE BUSES
  AND GOLF CARTS.

00:12:13.833 --> 00:12:15.702
GAVE THEM A LITTLE SPIEL
  ON THE BUS

00:12:15.768 --> 00:12:17.604
AND THEN TOOK THEM
  TO THE YACHT CLUB--

00:12:17.670 --> 00:12:19.372
AND HAD A MARINA THERE--

00:12:19.439 --> 00:12:23.476
AND HAD A NICE LUNCH
 AT THE YACHT CLUB.

00:12:26.879 --> 00:12:28.982
THE YACHT CLUB
WAS A BEAUTIFUL PLACE,

00:12:29.048 --> 00:12:30.550
HAD GOOD FOOD,

00:12:30.617 --> 00:12:34.721
HAD, MOST OF THE TIME,
 A VERY COMPETENT BARTENDER.

00:12:34.787 --> 00:12:36.623
HE KNEW HOW TO MAKE DRINKS,

00:12:36.689 --> 00:12:39.158
INSTEAD OF JUST
 SPLASHING THEM IN, YOU KNOW.

00:12:39.225 --> 00:12:42.095
COUPLE OF GOOD DRINKS,
 GOOD COMPANY,

00:12:42.161 --> 00:12:43.997
DO SOME DANCING.

00:12:48.901 --> 00:12:50.436
(* Music )

00:12:50.503 --> 00:12:52.272
Male Narrator:
  WHAT DOES MAN SEEK?

00:12:52.338 --> 00:12:55.408
WHATEVER IT IS,
  IT'S HERE AT SALTON CITY.

00:12:55.475 --> 00:12:57.443
HERE IS ALL THAT
  YOU AND YOUR FAMILY,

00:12:57.510 --> 00:13:00.346
YOUR CHILDREN AND YOUR
 CHILDREN'S CHILDREN WILL WANT.

00:13:00.413 --> 00:13:03.683
IN SPORTS, IN RELAXATION,
  IN PLEASURE, IN HEALTH,

00:13:03.750 --> 00:13:05.451
IN SECURITY.

00:13:05.518 --> 00:13:09.622
YES, AN INVESTMENT IN
  A GROWING PROSPEROUS FUTURE.

00:13:09.689 --> 00:13:14.494
THIS IS THE BIRTH OF A CITY,
  AN INVESTMENT IN THE FUTURE.

00:13:14.560 --> 00:13:16.963
THE FUTURE IS NOW.

00:13:17.030 --> 00:13:19.132
AND YOU...

00:13:19.198 --> 00:13:23.503
YOU HAVE BEEN PRESENT
  AT THE BIRTH OF A CITY.

00:13:29.509 --> 00:13:32.145
(* Music )

00:13:33.146 --> 00:13:37.083
Brian Napier:
  THE RISING SEA CAME
  PRIMARILY FROM ACCUSATIONS

00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:40.520
OF EXCESSIVE AGRICULTURAL
 RUNOFFS TO THE SOUTH.

00:13:40.586 --> 00:13:43.222
WHEN THE FARMERS ORDERED WATER,

00:13:43.289 --> 00:13:45.858
THEY WOULD ORDER ENOUGH
  TO BE SURE THEY HAD ENOUGH,

00:13:45.925 --> 00:13:49.128
AND THEY'D CLOSE THEIR GATES
 TO THEIR FARM

00:13:49.195 --> 00:13:50.463
WHEN THEY HAD ALL THEY WANTED,

00:13:50.530 --> 00:13:52.432
AND LET THE REST RUN OUT.

00:13:52.498 --> 00:13:54.567
AND IT CAME INTO THE SEA.

00:13:56.736 --> 00:13:59.972
WELL, THERE'S
 CONFLICTING STORIES

00:14:00.039 --> 00:14:01.974
ABOUT HOW IT HAPPENED,

00:14:02.041 --> 00:14:06.346
WHETHER IT WAS DELIBERATE
 OR NOT DELIBERATE OR WHAT.

00:14:06.412 --> 00:14:08.548
WHAT HAPPENED, I DON'T KNOW,
 BUT THE WATER ROSE.

00:14:11.284 --> 00:14:14.954
AND WE WERE SMACKED
 BY A PAIR OF TROPICAL STORMS,

00:14:15.021 --> 00:14:17.523
ONE IN '76, ONE IN '77,

00:14:17.590 --> 00:14:20.893
THAT DROPPED UNBELIEVABLE
 AMOUNTS OF RAINWATER

00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:23.196
ON THE IMPERIAL VALLEY.

00:14:25.598 --> 00:14:27.367
IT REALLY FLOODED THE SEA,

00:14:27.433 --> 00:14:30.837
SO WE STARTED SANDBAGGING,

00:14:30.903 --> 00:14:33.906
AND THAT WASN'T DOING
  MUCH GOOD EITHER.

00:14:33.973 --> 00:14:36.242
WE'D BE OUT--
 IT MIGHT BE MIDNIGHT.

00:14:36.309 --> 00:14:38.678
CREWS OF US WOULD BE
 OUT HERE SANDBAGGING,

00:14:38.745 --> 00:14:41.247
BECAUSE WATER
  WAS COMING OVER.

00:14:42.014 --> 00:14:43.383
WE HAD A FRIEND

00:14:43.449 --> 00:14:47.754
THAT LIVED BELOW 4th STREET
 IN A MOBILE HOME

00:14:47.820 --> 00:14:50.056
AND THE WATER WAS
  COMING IN HER FRONT DOOR,

00:14:50.123 --> 00:14:52.825
SO SHE BROUGHT HER DOG,
 AND HER CIGARETTES,

00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:54.360
AND HER BOTTLE OF BOOZE,

00:14:54.427 --> 00:14:58.164
AND CAME UP
AND WE SWEATED IT OUT.

00:14:58.231 --> 00:15:02.068
NOBODY GOT MAD OR SCARED
  AND RAN AWAY OR ANYTHING.

00:15:02.135 --> 00:15:04.337
B.L.M. TOLD US TO EVACUATE.

00:15:04.404 --> 00:15:07.306
WE SAID, "HUH-UNH.
  TOO MANY YEARS."

00:15:10.042 --> 00:15:14.514
IT TORE UP THE MARINA
 BY THE YACHT CLUB.

00:15:14.580 --> 00:15:16.816
JUST WASHED IT OUT TO SEA
  PRACTICALLY.

00:15:16.883 --> 00:15:18.785
WE PICKED UP PIECES OF IT.

00:15:18.851 --> 00:15:21.120
WHEN SOMETHING MAJOR
  LIKE THAT WENT OUT,

00:15:21.187 --> 00:15:24.123
THEY WEREN'T ABOUT
  THE REPLACE IT.

00:15:24.190 --> 00:15:30.062
IT WAS THE LAST VESTIGE
 OF THE GOOD TIMES DOWN HERE.

00:15:43.443 --> 00:15:45.011
John Waters:
 AS AN UNNATURAL BODY OF WATER,

00:15:45.077 --> 00:15:47.046
THE SEA IS LIKE
 A GIANT PUDDLE

00:15:47.113 --> 00:15:49.615
AT THE BOTTOM OF
  A DRAINED SWIMMING POOL.

00:15:49.682 --> 00:15:52.852
WITH NO OUTLET, THE WATER LEVEL
  CAN CHANGE SUDDENLY,

00:15:52.919 --> 00:15:56.522
AND ANYTHING THE WATER
  BRINGS IN, STAYS THERE.

00:15:56.589 --> 00:15:59.492
THE ONLY REASON
  THIS PUDDLE DOESN'T DRY UP,

00:15:59.559 --> 00:16:01.994
IS BECAUSE OF
  SALTY IRRIGATION RUNOFF

00:16:02.061 --> 00:16:04.030
FROM SURROUNDING FARMS.

00:16:04.096 --> 00:16:06.432
BUT WITH 6 FEET
 OF EVAPORATION A YEAR,

00:16:06.499 --> 00:16:08.134
THIS LIFE-SUSTAINING RUNOFF,

00:16:08.201 --> 00:16:11.537
IS CONCENTRATED
  INTO A SALTY SOUP.

00:16:11.604 --> 00:16:12.772
LET'S JUST SAY,

00:16:12.839 --> 00:16:15.641
IT'S NOT THE BEST SITUATION
 FOR THE FISH.

00:16:15.708 --> 00:16:17.543
(* Rock Music )

00:16:19.245 --> 00:16:22.882
Norm Niver:
  WALL-TO-WALL DEAD FISH,

00:16:22.949 --> 00:16:25.685
150 FEET OUT FROM MY DOCK

00:16:25.751 --> 00:16:28.087
AND ABOUT
 A QUARTER OF A MILE LONG.

00:16:35.695 --> 00:16:37.330
DURING THE SUMMER,

00:16:37.396 --> 00:16:40.399
THE WATER IN THE SALTON SEA
 IS SO WARM AND SO SALTY,

00:16:40.466 --> 00:16:43.569
THAT OXYGEN WILL HAVE
  A DIFFICULT TIME DISSOLVING.

00:16:43.636 --> 00:16:46.439
SO WE HAVE THESE
 LARGE DIE-OFFS OF TILAPIA

00:16:46.506 --> 00:16:47.807
JUST FOR THE SIMPLE REASON

00:16:47.874 --> 00:16:49.909
THAT THERE'S NO OXYGEN
  FOR THEM TO BREATHE.

00:16:49.976 --> 00:16:51.711
GOOD-BYE, FISH!
HA, HA!

00:16:51.777 --> 00:16:53.346
Steve Horvitz:
  AND THEY'LL DIE
  BY THE MILLIONS.

00:16:56.082 --> 00:17:01.721
THE DECAY DOES GET
PRETTY SMELLY AT TIMES.

00:17:01.787 --> 00:17:03.623
Norm Niver:
 WHEN THEY DIE,
  THEY ARE FERTILIZER.

00:17:03.689 --> 00:17:07.527
THEY ARE NUTRIENTS
  RETURNED TO THE SEA WATER.

00:17:07.593 --> 00:17:11.063
AND THE NUTRIENTS ARE SO HIGH
 THEY CREATE ALGAE BLOOMS.

00:17:11.130 --> 00:17:13.766
CONTINUOUS CYCLE OF FISH DYING,

00:17:13.833 --> 00:17:16.135
PROVIDING NUTRITION
FOR MORE ALGAE,

00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:18.070
WHICH MEANS MORE FISH.

00:17:18.137 --> 00:17:19.338
YOU KNOW, JUST--

00:17:19.405 --> 00:17:21.607
THERE'S JUST
 TOO MANY FISH HERE.

00:17:21.674 --> 00:17:24.143
THE SALTON SEA HAS ABOUT
 100 MILLION TILAPIA IN IT,

00:17:24.210 --> 00:17:26.245
WHICH IS A HUGE POPULATION.

00:17:26.312 --> 00:17:27.613
SOME PEOPLE THINK THAT IT'S

00:17:27.680 --> 00:17:30.583
THE MOST PRODUCTIVE
 TILAPIA RESOURCE,

00:17:30.650 --> 00:17:32.018
MAYBE EVEN IN THE WORLD.

00:17:32.084 --> 00:17:35.421
THE POPULATION OF THE FISH
IN HERE IS STUPENDOUS,

00:17:35.488 --> 00:17:38.291
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
 THE QUANTITY OF THE FISH--

00:17:38.357 --> 00:17:40.526
YOU SEE 'EM DYING
 ALL OVER THE PLACE

00:17:40.593 --> 00:17:42.628
AND YET YOU DON'T LOSE NONE.

00:17:42.695 --> 00:17:44.263
THEY'RE RIGHT BACK AGAIN
THE NEXT YEAR.

00:17:44.330 --> 00:17:47.767
THERE'S THOUSANDS
 AND THOUSANDS OF 'EM.

00:17:47.833 --> 00:17:48.901
AND YOU SEE 'EM SOMETIMES

00:17:48.968 --> 00:17:51.604
STACKED TWO AND THREE FEET HIGH
 ON THE BEACH

00:17:51.671 --> 00:17:53.172
WHEN THEY HAVE A DIE-OFF.

00:17:53.239 --> 00:17:54.307
BUT YOU GO OUT FISHING

00:17:54.373 --> 00:17:56.676
WHEN THE SEASON HITS
AND EVERYTHING

00:17:56.742 --> 00:17:59.011
AND IT'S FULL OF FISH.

00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:02.014
YEAH, SO WHAT CAN I SAY?

00:18:03.382 --> 00:18:05.484
(* Music )

00:18:18.564 --> 00:18:22.068
BY 1980,
 MOST PEOPLE HAD GIVEN UP

00:18:22.134 --> 00:18:24.770
ON ANY EXPLOSIVE GROWTH.

00:18:24.837 --> 00:18:27.173
THE BUILDING WAS LIMITED
 BY THE DEMAND,

00:18:27.239 --> 00:18:30.810
WHICH THERE WASN'T
  A GREAT DEAL OF.

00:18:30.876 --> 00:18:32.044
AND SEEING WHAT
  REAL ESTATE VALUES

00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:33.813
WERE STARTING TO DO THEN,

00:18:33.879 --> 00:18:36.716
"WE CAN'T LOSE."

00:18:36.782 --> 00:18:38.517
WELL, YOU CAN'T WIN, EITHER.
 ( Laughs )

00:18:38.584 --> 00:18:41.354
(* Music Continues )

00:18:48.327 --> 00:18:49.895
SALTON CITY,
UNFORTUNATELY,

00:18:49.962 --> 00:18:56.602
WAS DEVELOPED AS A PLACE
 TO MAKE MONEY BY BUYING A LOT.

00:18:56.669 --> 00:18:58.070
WITH THE WATER AND EVERYTHING,

00:18:58.137 --> 00:19:03.275
THIS WOULD BECOME A RESORT AREA
LIKE THE MEDITERRANEAN.

00:19:03.342 --> 00:19:05.745
AND YEARS AGO,
 IT HAD SORT OF A CHANCE,

00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:12.685
BUT THE--IF IT HAD BEEN BUILT
RATHER THAN SOLD LOTS.

00:19:12.752 --> 00:19:14.153
THE PROBLEM WAS, OF COURSE,

00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:18.491
THAT THEY SOLD IT
  TO PEOPLE WHO WERE GREEDY

00:19:18.557 --> 00:19:22.294
AND WANTED TO MAKE MONEY ON IT
RATHER THAN AS A PLACE TO LIVE.

00:19:23.362 --> 00:19:24.330
( Cash Register Dings )

00:19:24.397 --> 00:19:26.632
THIS IS THE LAST FRONTIER.

00:19:26.699 --> 00:19:30.302
IT'S THE LAST PLACE YOU CAN GO
 AND GET CHEAP LAND.

00:19:30.369 --> 00:19:32.438
AND I MEAN, CHEAP!

00:19:32.505 --> 00:19:38.711
ALL THESE LITTLE TEENY SQUARES
  IN HERE, ARE LOTS.

00:19:38.778 --> 00:19:43.282
THERE ARE 26,000 LOTS
  IN THIS SUBDIVISION.

00:19:43.349 --> 00:19:49.422
AND EVERY LOT HAS SEWER,

00:19:49.488 --> 00:19:52.258
IT'S ON THE SEWER,
 LIKE CITY SEWERAGE.

00:19:52.324 --> 00:19:56.462
CITY SEWER,
 HAVE WATER IN THE STREET,

00:19:56.529 --> 00:20:00.232
AND YOU PAY FOR
 A WATER METER TO HOOK UP,

00:20:00.299 --> 00:20:02.702
IF YOU ARE BUILDING,
  OR PUT A MOBILE HOME ON IT.

00:20:02.768 --> 00:20:05.471
IT HAS TO BE
  A DOUBLE-WIDE MOBILE HOME.

00:20:05.538 --> 00:20:08.374
AND, UM,
IT'S A FANTASTIC DEAL.

00:20:08.441 --> 00:20:11.777
YOU CAN BUY ONE
FOR $3500 CASH.

00:20:13.412 --> 00:20:16.015
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE RICH
 TO OWN A PIECE OF CALIFORNIA.

00:20:16.082 --> 00:20:18.551
SEE THE LANDMAN!

00:20:18.617 --> 00:20:20.820
Male Narrator:
  YOU CAN OWN A PIECE
 OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA

00:20:20.886 --> 00:20:22.888
FOR AS LITTLE AS
  $100 DOWN,

00:20:22.955 --> 00:20:24.290
AND MONTHLY PAYMENTS

00:20:24.356 --> 00:20:26.926
LESS THAN YOU WOULD SPEND
 ON YOUR ELECTRIC BILL.

00:20:26.992 --> 00:20:30.463
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE RICH,
 THE LANDMAN HAS THE ANSWER!

00:20:30.529 --> 00:20:33.933
WHEN I FIRST CAME HERE,
 I SAW THIS OPPORTUNITY--

00:20:33.999 --> 00:20:36.535
FIRST I SAW THE VIEW
AND SAID, "WOW!

00:20:36.602 --> 00:20:39.739
THERE IT IS!
 UNIQUE, THIS THING."

00:20:39.805 --> 00:20:41.640
THE NEXT THING
 THAT CAME TO MY MIND,

00:20:41.707 --> 00:20:43.542
"DOLLARS, DOLLARS, DOLLARS!

00:20:43.609 --> 00:20:46.679
MAN, I GOT TO COME HERE
 AND MAKE A FORTUNE!"

00:20:46.746 --> 00:20:49.982
HASTA MI BEBITA SABE
 UN BUEN NEGOCIO CUANDO LO VEA.

00:20:50.049 --> 00:20:51.617
SEE THE LANDMAN!

00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:54.253
YOU KNOW, PEOPLE
 IN THE LAND BUSINESS,

00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:56.155
THEY TALK ABOUT
THE SALTON SEA.

00:20:56.222 --> 00:20:57.723
IT'S A LEGEND.

00:20:57.790 --> 00:21:02.595
IT'S A LEGEND OF FAILURE, OF
 HORRIBLE THINGS THAT HAPPENED.

00:21:02.661 --> 00:21:05.598
AND I CAME HERE
 AND I SAW EVERYTHING.

00:21:05.664 --> 00:21:07.933
I SAW THE VIEW,
I SAW THE SEA,

00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:09.635
I SAW EVERYTHING
 THAT WAS HAPPENING,

00:21:09.702 --> 00:21:11.537
AND I THOUGHT IT WAS
A HUMONGOUS OPPORTUNITY

00:21:11.604 --> 00:21:14.774
TO CHANGE PEOPLE'S
PERCEPTION OF THE SEA.

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:16.809
(* Music )

00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.814
EVEN IF YOU DON'T
 WANT TO BUILD RIGHT NOW,

00:21:21.881 --> 00:21:25.151
IT'S GOING TO
 ACCELERATE IN VALUE,

00:21:25.217 --> 00:21:26.519
IT HAS TO.

00:21:26.585 --> 00:21:28.687
AND WHEN IT HAPPENS,
 I DON'T KNOW,

00:21:28.754 --> 00:21:31.557
BUT IT WILL HAPPEN.

00:21:31.624 --> 00:21:32.892
YOU HAVE A LOT OF PEOPLE

00:21:32.958 --> 00:21:34.693
THAT ARE WAITING
 FOR THINGS TO HAPPEN,

00:21:34.760 --> 00:21:37.596
AND THEY ALL FEEL LIKE
 IT'S JUST AROUND THE CORNER.

00:21:37.663 --> 00:21:38.998
AND THEY HAVE PROBABLY
 BEEN FEELING LIKE

00:21:39.064 --> 00:21:40.833
IT'S JUST AROUND THE CORNER
 FOR 10 OR 15 YEARS.

00:21:44.036 --> 00:21:48.574
I-I'VE ALWAYS THOUGHT
 THE SEA WOULD GROW,

00:21:48.641 --> 00:21:51.410
WOULD DO SOMETHING.

00:21:51.477 --> 00:21:52.645
IT'S TAKEN LONGER
THAN I THOUGHT,

00:21:52.711 --> 00:21:55.414
BUT IN THE MEANTIME,

00:21:55.481 --> 00:21:57.683
IF PROPERTY COMES UP FOR SALE
AND THE PRICE IS RIGHT,

00:21:57.750 --> 00:21:59.084
I BUY IT.

00:22:00.286 --> 00:22:04.056
I HAVEN'T OVERPAID
FOR ANY OF IT,

00:22:04.123 --> 00:22:09.161
BUT--IT'S AN INVESTMENT.

00:22:09.228 --> 00:22:12.298
PEOPLE ARE BUYING
AND LIKE TO SPECULATE, YOU KNOW.

00:22:12.364 --> 00:22:13.799
IF THEY PLAY THE LOTTERY,

00:22:13.866 --> 00:22:16.936
THEY SHOULD AT LEAST GET
A $400 LOT OUT HERE SOMEPLACE.

00:22:17.002 --> 00:22:18.971
( Laughs )

00:22:19.038 --> 00:22:22.508
BUT THERE'S STILL A LOT OF LOTS
 OUT HERE FOR SALE.

00:22:22.575 --> 00:22:24.510
(* Music )

00:22:29.048 --> 00:22:32.852
THE MATERIAL IS HERE,
 BUT IT TAKES A LOT OF WORK.

00:22:32.918 --> 00:22:34.920
BUT I THINK IT'LL BE WORTH IT
 IN THE END.

00:22:34.987 --> 00:22:39.291
I'M JUST SORRY THAT I WON'T BE
 HERE TO SEE IT, PROBABLY.

00:22:39.358 --> 00:22:42.194
MY LIFE EXPECTANCY IS,
 I GUESS, AROUND 11 YEARS,

00:22:42.261 --> 00:22:43.629
SOMETHING LIKE THAT,

00:22:43.696 --> 00:22:50.336
AND I DON'T EXPECT
 TO SEE MIRACLES IN THAT TIME.

00:22:54.573 --> 00:22:57.209
(* Blues Music )

00:23:02.147 --> 00:23:04.617
John Waters:
  WHILE MANY CONTINUE
 TO WAIT FOR THE DREAM,

00:23:04.683 --> 00:23:06.819
ACROSS THE SEA
  IN THE WORKING-CLASS HAVEN

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.153
OF BOMBAY BEACH,

00:23:08.220 --> 00:23:11.190
PEOPLE HAVE ALREADY
  FOUND PARADISE.

00:23:11.257 --> 00:23:12.558
BUT HALF-FLOODED,

00:23:12.625 --> 00:23:14.760
WITH NO GAS STATION,
  ONE TINY STORE,

00:23:14.827 --> 00:23:16.262
TWO DELIGHTFUL BARS,

00:23:16.328 --> 00:23:18.464
AND AN OBSESSION
  WITH GOLF CARTS,

00:23:18.530 --> 00:23:22.001
THIS DUSTY LITTLE TOWN
 ISN'T EVERYONE'S IDEA

00:23:22.067 --> 00:23:24.403
OF WHAT THE DREAM
  WAS SUPPOSED TO BECOME.

00:23:25.271 --> 00:23:29.475
THIS WHOLE AREA DOWN HERE
BELOW THE DIKE WAS FLOODED OUT.

00:23:32.211 --> 00:23:34.780
RIGHT OVER THERE,
  WHAT'S LEFT OF THE BUILDING

00:23:34.847 --> 00:23:38.317
IS WHAT USED TO BE
  THE "LUCK OF THE IRISH."

00:23:38.384 --> 00:23:39.919
AND OVER THERE,
 WHERE IT'S FENCED,

00:23:39.985 --> 00:23:42.821
THERE USED TO BE A BEER BAR
  CALLED "THE WATERFRONT"

00:23:42.888 --> 00:23:44.890
AND A FISHING PIER.

00:23:44.957 --> 00:23:47.760
BUT IT'S ALL GONE.

00:23:47.826 --> 00:23:50.296
(* Blues Music )

00:23:53.299 --> 00:23:54.733
THE OLD PEOPLE,

00:23:54.800 --> 00:23:56.235
THEY STAY IN THEIR HOUSE
 DURING THE DAYTIME

00:23:56.302 --> 00:23:58.003
AND THEY COME OUT AT NIGHT.

00:23:58.070 --> 00:24:00.039
MOST OF 'EM DO ANYWAY.

00:24:00.105 --> 00:24:01.740
GUY SHOT HISSELF IN THE HEAD
 RIGHT THERE.

00:24:01.807 --> 00:24:04.843
THERE'S ONE DOWN THE STREET
 WHERE A GUY HUNG HISSELF.

00:24:04.910 --> 00:24:06.812
AND THIS ONE
 ON THE CORNER RIGHT THERE,

00:24:06.879 --> 00:24:11.350
HE DIED TRYING TO TAKE A POOP
RIGHT THERE IN HIS HOUSE.

00:24:11.417 --> 00:24:15.654
COUPLE OF STROKES
 AND OLD AGE THINGS...

00:24:15.721 --> 00:24:16.889
BRAIN TUMOR

00:24:16.956 --> 00:24:19.325
AND ARTERY BYPASS,
YOU KNOW, JUST...

00:24:19.391 --> 00:24:20.926
IN MY HOUSE,
 A PERSON DIED OVER THERE.

00:24:20.993 --> 00:24:22.661
IN THIS ONE, TOO,
 MY BEST FRIEND'S, DIED--

00:24:22.728 --> 00:24:23.963
THAT'S OVER THERE,
 YOU KNOW.

00:24:24.029 --> 00:24:25.831
A LOT OF PEOPLE
 HAVE DIED OUT HERE.

00:24:25.898 --> 00:24:28.567
I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S
 FROM OLD AGE OR,

00:24:28.634 --> 00:24:32.137
YOU KNOW, BECAUSE OF,
 YOU KNOW, THE CONDITIONS,

00:24:32.204 --> 00:24:33.572
OR WHAT.

00:24:33.639 --> 00:24:37.176
I HAD A LITTLE PROBLEM WHEN WE
WERE WORKING AT DESERT HOSPITAL,

00:24:37.242 --> 00:24:38.744
A LITTLE CANCER PROBLEM.

00:24:38.811 --> 00:24:40.079
AND I SAID, "THAT'S IT.

00:24:40.145 --> 00:24:42.548
I'M NOT WORKING ANYMORE."

00:24:42.614 --> 00:24:45.117
YOU KNOW, WHO KNOWS,
MAYBE TOMORROW, MAYBE--

00:24:45.184 --> 00:24:47.953
AND THAT'S BEEN 20 YEARS AGO.

00:24:48.020 --> 00:24:51.390
SO I BLAME MY GOOD HEALTH
 ON THE SALTON SEA.

00:24:51.457 --> 00:24:52.658
( Laughs )

00:24:52.725 --> 00:24:55.794
(* Blues Continue )

00:25:01.734 --> 00:25:04.370
WE HAVE LOTS OF YARD SALES.

00:25:04.436 --> 00:25:08.941
THAT LADY'S HUSBAND DIED
AND SHE'S MOVING SO...

00:25:09.008 --> 00:25:11.477
THEN WE WORRY ABOUT THINGS
 LIKE THIS,

00:25:11.543 --> 00:25:13.579
BECAUSE OF THE KIDS.

00:25:13.645 --> 00:25:17.616
THEY GET IN
 AND SMOKE THE GRASS AND--

00:25:17.683 --> 00:25:19.385
YOU KNOW,
 SOME OF THE BLACK KIDS

00:25:19.451 --> 00:25:22.921
ARE JUST DELIGHTFUL.

00:25:22.988 --> 00:25:27.159
BUT THERE'S A GROUP
THAT ARE...IN TROUBLE.

00:25:29.094 --> 00:25:32.698
LOOK AT THAT RIDICULOUS
WINDMILL HOUSE!

00:25:34.266 --> 00:25:37.703
PEOPLE COME IN FROM L.A.
 THAT CAUSE A LOT OF PROBLEMS,

00:25:37.770 --> 00:25:39.038
ROBBING HOUSES,

00:25:39.104 --> 00:25:44.443
AND, YOU KNOW, SELLING DRUGS
 AND STUFF LIKE THAT.

00:25:44.510 --> 00:25:49.048
THERE'S MORE WELFARE PEOPLE
 HERE NOW.

00:25:49.114 --> 00:25:51.950
THE RENT'S CHEAPER HERE, SO...

00:25:52.017 --> 00:25:55.821
THE COUNTY SENDS 'EM OUT HERE.

00:25:55.888 --> 00:25:57.890
WHEN THE YOUNG KIDS
 COME IN HERE,

00:25:57.956 --> 00:25:59.992
THEY DON'T DO NOTHING
BUT RAISE HELL.

00:26:00.059 --> 00:26:02.861
( Glass Shattering )

00:26:02.928 --> 00:26:05.697
AND I TELL THEM,
 "I'M GONNA CALL A COP ON YA."

00:26:05.764 --> 00:26:08.067
"WHAT'S A COP GONNA DO?

00:26:08.133 --> 00:26:10.269
MAYBE BRING ME A LOLLIPOP?"

00:26:10.335 --> 00:26:12.137
YEAH, HA, HA.

00:26:12.204 --> 00:26:14.840
THEY CAN'T DO NOTHING, NAH-UH.

00:26:14.907 --> 00:26:17.709
AND THEIR PARENTS,
 THEY DON'T TEACH 'EM NOTHING.

00:26:17.776 --> 00:26:20.612
( Excited Chatter )

00:26:25.651 --> 00:26:27.086
I DON'T KNOW,
 I LIVED OUT HERE SO LONG

00:26:27.152 --> 00:26:29.088
TO WHERE I'M JUST
 KINDA USED TO IT.

00:26:29.154 --> 00:26:32.458
IT'S KINDA BORING OUT HERE,
BUT IT'S COOL.

00:26:32.524 --> 00:26:33.592
Lechon Rainey:
IT'S AWAY FROM THE CITY.

00:26:33.659 --> 00:26:35.160
YOU AIN'T GOT TO WORRY
ABOUT GANG-BANGING,

00:26:35.227 --> 00:26:37.596
YOU AIN'T GOT TO WORRY ABOUT
 NONE OF THAT STUFF OUT HERE.

00:26:37.663 --> 00:26:38.897
ONLY ONE PROBLEM WE HAVE

00:26:38.964 --> 00:26:40.399
IS THEY NEED TO CLEAN UP
THAT OUT THERE

00:26:40.466 --> 00:26:42.234
SO EVERYBODY, YOU KNOW,
 HAVE SOMETHING TO DO,

00:26:42.301 --> 00:26:43.769
BESIDES FISHING.

00:26:43.836 --> 00:26:46.271
YOU KNOW, NOBODY WANT TO EAT
 THAT STUFF OUT OF THERE.

00:26:46.338 --> 00:26:49.508
AND, YOU KNOW, OUT HERE
IT AIN'T, I DON'T KNOW--

00:26:49.575 --> 00:26:51.610
SEE ALL THESE KIDS OUT HERE?

00:26:51.677 --> 00:26:53.078
WE NEED SOMETHING
 FOR THE KIDS.

00:26:53.145 --> 00:26:55.214
AS YOU CAN SEE,
  WE ONLY GOT ONE LITTLE PARK,

00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:57.583
AND THAT'S REALLY ABOUT IT.

00:26:57.649 --> 00:26:59.852
MY MOM, MY BIOLOGICAL MOM,

00:26:59.918 --> 00:27:01.587
GOT SHOT AND KILLED
 BY HER BOYFRIEND,

00:27:01.653 --> 00:27:04.189
AND MY MOM'S SISTER
  TOOK CARE OF US.

00:27:04.256 --> 00:27:06.825
AND EL CENTRO
 WAS TOO ROUGH FOR US,

00:27:06.892 --> 00:27:08.527
SO SHE MOVED US OUT HERE.

00:27:08.594 --> 00:27:09.795
WHEN SHE MOVED US OUT HERE,

00:27:09.862 --> 00:27:12.030
YOU KNOW, HEY,
THINGS HAPPEN, I GOT PREGNANT.

00:27:12.097 --> 00:27:13.599
I CHOOSE TO RAISE MY SON
 OUT HERE.

00:27:13.665 --> 00:27:15.200
I'M NOT GOING TO TAKE HIM
 TO EL CENTRO AND RAISE HIM,

00:27:15.267 --> 00:27:17.769
I AM GOING TO RAISE HIM
  RIGHT HERE ON BOMBAY BEACH.

00:27:17.836 --> 00:27:18.804
THERE AIN'T NOTHING
  OUT HERE,

00:27:18.871 --> 00:27:20.639
NO VIOLENCE,
 NONE OF THAT.

00:27:20.706 --> 00:27:21.940
YOU KNOW WHAT I AM SAYING?

00:27:22.007 --> 00:27:23.609
IT'S A RETIRING PLACE,
  IT'S FOR OLD PEOPLE.

00:27:23.675 --> 00:27:25.077
IF YOU RAISE 'EM UP
 IN THE CITY,

00:27:25.144 --> 00:27:28.013
THEY'LL BE EITHER GANG-BANGING,
 SHOOTING EACH OTHER.

00:27:28.080 --> 00:27:29.348
I MEAN, HATRED.

00:27:29.414 --> 00:27:30.816
I MEAN, THAT'S IF
YOU RAISE THEM UP IN THE CITY,

00:27:30.883 --> 00:27:32.518
BUT IF YOU RAISE THEM UP
 IN BOMBAY BEACH,

00:27:32.584 --> 00:27:35.754
YOUR KIDS WON'T BE
 GROWING UP LIKE THAT.

00:27:35.821 --> 00:27:37.089
IN THE CITY,
 HE'LL GET SHOT AND KILLED

00:27:37.156 --> 00:27:39.057
IN LESS THAN 48 HOURS.

00:27:39.124 --> 00:27:41.660
UP HERE, HE'LL HAVE
 A BETTER CHANCE OF LIVIN'.

00:27:41.727 --> 00:27:44.630
( Excited Chatter )

00:27:44.696 --> 00:27:47.366
EVERYBODY GETS WEED AROUND HER,

00:27:47.432 --> 00:27:49.101
BUT WHEN THEY ASK ME FOR SOME,

00:27:49.168 --> 00:27:51.170
OR FLAUBERT OR ANYBODY,

00:27:51.236 --> 00:27:53.338
THEY SAY NO.

00:27:53.405 --> 00:27:56.675
'CAUSE WE KNOW OUR RESPECTS,
 WE KNOW.

00:27:56.742 --> 00:27:58.043
BOMBAY BEACH TREAT ME GOOD!

00:27:58.110 --> 00:28:00.979
THEY GOT ALL THE 40s
 AND ALL THE WEED!

00:28:01.046 --> 00:28:04.349
GOD DIED FOR OUR SINS!

00:28:04.416 --> 00:28:06.318
SO I'M NOT GOING TO FOOL GOD
 LIKE THAT

00:28:06.385 --> 00:28:10.556
AND JUST KEEP ON DOING STUFF,
 LIKE DRUGS AND STUFF.

00:28:10.622 --> 00:28:11.823
I AIN'T GONNA DO THAT.

00:28:11.890 --> 00:28:12.891
Flaubert:
 I AIN'T DOIN' THAT.

00:28:12.958 --> 00:28:17.229
ANYBODY ASK ME FOR DRUGS,
MAN...HECK NO!

00:28:17.296 --> 00:28:20.132
I AIN'T WITH THAT DOPE BOY!

00:28:20.199 --> 00:28:21.633
Jeff Springer:
  HOW ABOUT SOCCER, YOU GUYS?

00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:24.336
SOCCER! OH YEAH!
THAT'S MY STUFF!

00:28:24.403 --> 00:28:26.772
THAT'S MY SPORT!
THAT'S MY SPORT!

00:28:26.838 --> 00:28:31.577
BASKETBALL, FOOTBALL,
 BASEBALL; ALL THAT STUFF!

00:28:31.643 --> 00:28:32.945
VOLLEYBALL!

00:28:34.613 --> 00:28:35.881
John Waters:
 FORGOTTEN AND FLOODED,

00:28:35.948 --> 00:28:37.950
BOMBAY BEACH
 IS THE PERFECT REFUGE

00:28:38.016 --> 00:28:39.484
FROM THE OUTSIDE WORLD.

00:28:39.551 --> 00:28:41.486
BUT WHEN YOU LIVE
  IN A TRAILER PARK

00:28:41.553 --> 00:28:44.089
ON THE EDGE
  OF AN ECOLOGICAL TIME BOMB,

00:28:44.156 --> 00:28:47.259
YOU GOTTA HAVE SOME FUN,
  AND DRINK PLENTY OF BEER.

00:28:48.527 --> 00:28:50.562
Lechon:
 EVERYBODY, WATCH HUNKY DADDY.

00:28:50.629 --> 00:28:51.964
Olivia Benitez:
 THIS IS HUNKY DADDY,

00:28:52.030 --> 00:28:54.633
OUR FAVORITE GUY IN THE TOWN!

00:28:54.700 --> 00:28:56.335
THIS IS MY GUY!

00:28:59.805 --> 00:29:01.540
Olivia:
 AND THIS IS THEIR OTHER DOG!

00:29:03.709 --> 00:29:05.544
THIS IS A BABY BOY.

00:29:05.611 --> 00:29:06.979
THAT OVER THERE'S THE GIRL--

00:29:07.045 --> 00:29:10.549
SHE HAD BABIES,
AND SHE IS PRETTY, TOO.

00:29:10.616 --> 00:29:11.483
I LIKE HER.

00:29:11.550 --> 00:29:12.784
THEY ARE VERY FRIENDLY.

00:29:22.527 --> 00:29:26.531
LES, HE'S ONE OF A KIND,
 THAT'S FOR SURE.

00:29:32.771 --> 00:29:34.406
THAT'S EMBARRASSING!

00:29:36.642 --> 00:29:37.976
Olivia:
  BYE, HUNKY DADDY!

00:29:38.043 --> 00:29:39.911
THAT'S MY GUY
  RIGHT HERE!

00:29:39.978 --> 00:29:41.346
WHOO!

00:29:42.347 --> 00:29:45.851
HE'S, UH...

00:29:45.917 --> 00:29:47.619
( Laughs )
 WHAT CAN I SAY ABOUT HIM?

00:29:47.686 --> 00:29:49.087
HE'S NUTS!
 ( Laughs )

00:29:53.458 --> 00:29:55.093
HE'S, UH...HE'S WILD!

00:29:56.328 --> 00:29:57.296
HE'S A WILD CHILD!

00:30:02.401 --> 00:30:03.935
HE LOVES WOMEN, ALL WOMEN,

00:30:04.002 --> 00:30:07.306
I DON'T CARE WHAT THEY ARE,
 BLACK, WHITE, YELLOW, GREEN.

00:30:07.372 --> 00:30:09.207
HE LOVES 'EM ALL!

00:30:11.910 --> 00:30:13.712
THERE'S A LOT OF HUNGARIANS
 IN BOMBAY,

00:30:13.779 --> 00:30:15.914
THEY SEEM TO LIKE THE--

00:30:15.981 --> 00:30:18.317
WELL, ALL HUNGARIANS
 LIKE TO PARTY, I MUST SAY.

00:30:18.383 --> 00:30:19.851
SOME PEOPLE CALL THEM
 HUNGARIANS,

00:30:19.918 --> 00:30:21.553
BUT YA PAY ATTENTION
 TO THEIR LANGUAGE

00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:23.455
AND I'LL BET YA
 THEY'RE SPEAKIN' RUSSIAN.

00:30:23.522 --> 00:30:25.090
YOU KNOW,
 MY DAD MOVED THERE,

00:30:25.157 --> 00:30:27.125
AND THEN ZOLI BOTCHY
 MOVED THERE,

00:30:27.192 --> 00:30:28.660
AND LOUIE MOVED THERE,

00:30:28.727 --> 00:30:30.562
AND YOSHKA JOE,
 HE MOVED THERE--

00:30:30.629 --> 00:30:32.998
THEY'RE ALL DEAD,
 ALL OF THEM DIED.

00:30:33.065 --> 00:30:36.001
AND THEN THERE WAS LES,
 AND SEGON AND...

00:30:36.068 --> 00:30:37.269
YEAH, THERE'S A BUNCH OF 'EM.

00:30:37.336 --> 00:30:38.937
THERE'S ONE THERE,
 THERE'S ONE THERE.

00:30:39.004 --> 00:30:41.306
THERE WAS ONE OVER,
 ACROSS THE STREET THERE.

00:30:41.373 --> 00:30:45.377
THERE ARE KIDS LIKE ME,
 LANKA AND ANIKO AND--

00:30:45.444 --> 00:30:46.778
GOD, THERE'S A LOT
 OF HUNGARIANS,

00:30:46.845 --> 00:30:47.846
I'M TELLING YA!

00:30:54.753 --> 00:30:56.088
Male Narrator:
  ALMOST WITH BARE HANDS,

00:30:56.154 --> 00:30:57.989
PATRIOTS
  JOINED BY THE HUNGARIAN ARMY

00:30:58.056 --> 00:30:59.491
ROSE SPONTANEOUSLY

00:30:59.558 --> 00:31:02.194
AND MADE A SHAMBLES
  OF THE MIGHTY RUSSIAN TANKS.

00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:05.097
FOR 10 DAYS THEY SENT
 THE RED MIGHT REELING.

00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:20.912
Male Narrator:
  BUT RETRIBUTION WAS SWIFT
 AND CRUSHING.

00:31:20.979 --> 00:31:23.148
TWENTY NEW DIVISIONS OF TANKS
  MOVED IN.

00:31:23.215 --> 00:31:24.483
THIS TIME,

00:31:24.549 --> 00:31:25.851
SHAKEN KREMLIN LEADERS
  TOOK NO CHANCES

00:31:25.917 --> 00:31:27.419
AND REBELLION
  TURNED TO SLAUGHTER

00:31:27.486 --> 00:31:28.687
IN THE UNEQUAL STRUGGLE.

00:31:48.540 --> 00:31:49.975
( Explosions )

00:31:55.313 --> 00:31:57.215
YEAH, HE WAS
 A FREEDOM FIGHTER.

00:31:57.282 --> 00:31:59.484
I NEVER SAW ANY PICTURES
 OF HIM IN UNIFORM,

00:31:59.551 --> 00:32:01.353
YOU KNOW,
 I KNOW HE WAS IN THE WAR,

00:32:01.420 --> 00:32:04.156
BUT I NEVER SAW
ANY PICTURES OF HIM IN UNIFORM.

00:32:04.222 --> 00:32:05.690
SO I GUESS

00:32:05.757 --> 00:32:07.893
THAT HE SAVED PEOPLE'S LIVES
 UNDERGROUND OR WHATEVER,

00:32:07.959 --> 00:32:09.761
AND THEN HE CAME TO AMERICA

00:32:09.828 --> 00:32:13.265
AND HE LOVED THIS...
 DESOLATE DESERT.

00:32:43.462 --> 00:32:45.297
(* Music )

00:32:52.204 --> 00:32:55.540
IT'S HURT ALL THE BUSINESS
AROUND THE VALLEY HERE.

00:32:55.607 --> 00:32:58.276
ALL THE BOAT LANDINGS
 HAVE CLOSED

00:32:58.343 --> 00:33:00.245
'CAUSE
 THERE WASN'T ANY BUSINESS.

00:33:00.312 --> 00:33:02.214
YOU KNOW WHAT?
 IF THEY'D DO THE SALTON SEA,

00:33:02.280 --> 00:33:03.782
EVERYTHING'LL BE
SO MUCH BETTER.

00:33:03.849 --> 00:33:05.517
AND PROPERTY TAXES WILL GO UP.

00:33:05.584 --> 00:33:06.885
AND THERE'S JUST--

00:33:06.952 --> 00:33:08.386
LOOK IT, WE'RE OUT
 IN THE MIDDLE OF THIS DESERT,

00:33:08.453 --> 00:33:09.688
WHERE IT GETS 120,

00:33:09.754 --> 00:33:12.891
WITH THIS HUGE BODY OF WATER
THAT WE CAN'T EVEN USE!

00:33:12.958 --> 00:33:15.494
IT'S ABSOLUTELY RIDICULOUS;
 IT MAKES ME SICK.

00:33:16.795 --> 00:33:20.565
EVERYTHING'S BUILT UP
 IN BIG CITIES NOW.

00:33:20.632 --> 00:33:22.067
IT HAS TO GO SOMEWHERE.

00:33:22.133 --> 00:33:23.869
IT HAS TO COME THIS WAY.

00:33:23.935 --> 00:33:26.571
WHERE ELSE CAN THEY GO?

00:33:26.638 --> 00:33:29.241
THIS'LL BE A WINTER RESORT
 DOWN HERE

00:33:29.307 --> 00:33:32.978
BEFORE TOO MANY YEARS I THINK.

00:33:33.044 --> 00:33:36.348
IT USED TO BE
 A NICE LITTLE TOWN.

00:33:36.414 --> 00:33:39.484
BUT NOW THEY'RE TRYING
 TO MAKE SOMETHING OUT OF IT,

00:33:39.551 --> 00:33:41.920
BUT THEY NEVER WILL.

00:33:41.987 --> 00:33:43.288
AND YOU CAN'T TAKE NOTHING,

00:33:43.355 --> 00:33:45.824
AND MAKE ANYTHING
  OUT OF NOTHING.

00:33:46.992 --> 00:33:50.095
John Waters:
  ONCE A STATION FOR THOUSANDS
  OF VACATIONING FISHERMAN

00:33:50.161 --> 00:33:52.497
COMING TO THE SALTON SEA,

00:33:52.564 --> 00:33:55.267
NILAND NOW BARELY HANGS ON.

00:33:55.333 --> 00:33:58.036
ITS ONLY SALVATION
  LIES IN THE CONSTRUCTION

00:33:58.103 --> 00:34:01.172
OF A VERY DIFFERENT KIND
 OF TOURIST ATTRACTION.

00:34:02.140 --> 00:34:04.576
LEONARD KNIGHT CAME HERE
 ABOUT 10 YEARS AGO

00:34:04.643 --> 00:34:05.911
AND STARTED BUILDING
THAT MOUNTAIN.

00:34:05.977 --> 00:34:08.179
HE'S WORKING ON IT
EVER SINCE, EVERY DAY.

00:34:08.246 --> 00:34:10.315
HE COMES IN HERE
 EVERY MORNING EARLY,

00:34:10.382 --> 00:34:12.918
STAYS AN HOUR OR SO
AND HAS COFFEE WITH US.

00:34:12.984 --> 00:34:15.120
HE'S A GOOD MAN.

00:34:15.186 --> 00:34:18.423
HE'S RELIGIOUS,
 BUT HE DOESN'T PUSH IT ON YOU.

00:34:18.490 --> 00:34:20.659
YOU CAN BE AS RELIGIOUS
AS YOU WANT TO,

00:34:20.725 --> 00:34:24.763
AS LONG AS YOU DON'T TRY
TO PUSH HIM INTO YOUR RELIGION.

00:34:24.829 --> 00:34:26.364
( Laughs )

00:34:26.431 --> 00:34:28.733
(* Music )

00:34:38.310 --> 00:34:41.179
Leonard Knight:
  I JUST BELIEVE THAT GOD
  REALLY BUILT THIS MOUNTAIN,

00:34:41.246 --> 00:34:44.749
I DIDN'T.

00:34:44.816 --> 00:34:48.720
I'M NOT REALLY CAPABLE OF--
  ESPECIALLY BEING AN ARTIST--

00:34:48.787 --> 00:34:50.855
I'M JUST NOT CAPABLE
 OF DOING ANYTHING,

00:34:50.922 --> 00:34:53.258
BUT GOD ALMIGHTY
 CAN DO ANYTHING.

00:34:53.325 --> 00:34:56.494
AND IF I'VE TALKED
 TO GOD A LOT,

00:34:56.561 --> 00:34:58.530
AND I KEEP SAYING
 ALMOST EVERY MORNING,

00:34:58.597 --> 00:35:00.966
"GOD, USE ME IF YOU CAN.

00:35:01.032 --> 00:35:02.500
I WANT TO WORK FOR YOU, GOD."

00:35:02.567 --> 00:35:03.635
AND LOOK AT THE MOUNTAIN,

00:35:03.702 --> 00:35:05.470
IT'S GOING BETTER THAN
  10 CHURCHES

00:35:05.537 --> 00:35:08.740
ALL PUT TOGETHER SOMETIMES.

00:35:08.807 --> 00:35:10.375
YOU KNOW,
  WHEN IT COMES TO PAINT--

00:35:10.442 --> 00:35:13.612
I JUST LOVE PAINT--OLD PAINT,
  NEW PAINT, PRETTY PAINT.

00:35:13.678 --> 00:35:15.280
AND I LIKE LATEX AT FIRST.

00:35:15.347 --> 00:35:18.116
IF I GET A PRETTY COLOR
 OF OIL HIGH-GLOSS PAINT,

00:35:18.183 --> 00:35:20.619
I KEEP IT FOR THE FLOWERS.

00:35:20.685 --> 00:35:25.223
SO, NO MATTER WHAT COMES IN,
 I'M EXCITED ABOUT IT. HA!

00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:27.392
PEOPLE JUST BRING ME
  THEIR PAINT.

00:35:27.459 --> 00:35:29.094
AND I LIKE TO GIVE POSTCARDS
  TO PEOPLE,

00:35:29.160 --> 00:35:30.829
SO IT'S A "GIVE ME" MOUNTAIN.

00:35:34.132 --> 00:35:36.368
NO EDUCATION FROM MAN
  WHATSOEVER.

00:35:36.434 --> 00:35:38.570
SO, IF THERE IS ANY PART
  OF THIS MOUNTAIN,

00:35:38.637 --> 00:35:40.372
IT'S NOT--I DIDN'T READ IT
  IN A BOOK,

00:35:40.438 --> 00:35:43.708
OR I DIDN'T PUSH
  AN INTERNET PUSH BUTTON.

00:35:43.775 --> 00:35:47.345
AND NOW PEOPLE REALLY THINK
I'M AN ARTIST.

00:35:47.412 --> 00:35:50.148
I HOPE I AM NOT A COUNTERFEIT.
 ( Laughs )

00:35:52.550 --> 00:35:54.853
YOU LEARN BY MISTAKES MAINLY.

00:35:54.919 --> 00:35:58.423
YOU MAKE A MISTAKE,
AND YOU KINDA HAVE FUN DOING IT,

00:35:58.490 --> 00:35:59.457
BUT THEN YOU LOOK BACK
 AND SAY,

00:35:59.524 --> 00:36:02.694
"HEY, THERE MUST BE
A BETTER WAY."

00:36:02.761 --> 00:36:05.030
I MADE ONE MISTAKE
  THAT TOOK ME FOUR YEARS--

00:36:05.096 --> 00:36:07.165
AND THE WHOLE MOUNTAIN
 FELL ON ME.

00:36:07.232 --> 00:36:10.101
SO I DON'T WANT TO MAKE
 MISTAKES THAT BIG ANYMORE.

00:36:10.168 --> 00:36:12.170
AT FIRST
 I DIDN'T BUILD IT RIGHT.

00:36:12.237 --> 00:36:14.472
AND I WENT TO THE DUMP,

00:36:14.539 --> 00:36:17.375
AND THEN I'D GET
  A REFRIGERATOR, TRUCK TIRES,

00:36:17.442 --> 00:36:19.144
AND I'D FILL 'EM WITH SAND

00:36:19.210 --> 00:36:22.147
AND PUT 'EM IN HERE
 AND PUT SOME CEMENT WITH IT.

00:36:22.213 --> 00:36:25.984
AND IN 1991,
 THE WHOLE MOUNTAIN FELL DOWN.

00:36:26.051 --> 00:36:29.554
I PROBABLY HAD 200 OR 300 TONS
  OF ADOBE UP HERE.

00:36:29.621 --> 00:36:33.758
AND IT WAS ABOUT THAT TIME,
I LOOKED UP AND I SAYS,

00:36:33.825 --> 00:36:38.063
"GOD, YOU BUILD THE MOUNTAIN,
JUST DON'T LET LEONARD BUILD IT.

00:36:38.129 --> 00:36:39.297
GOD, YOU DO IT."

00:36:39.364 --> 00:36:41.700
AND, BOY, EVER SINCE THEN--

00:36:41.766 --> 00:36:43.968
I JUST STARTED DIGGING
 IN THIS MOUNTAIN,

00:36:44.035 --> 00:36:46.471
AND I'VE BEEN TOTALLY HAPPY
 EVER SINCE.

00:36:49.908 --> 00:36:55.747
THE SALTON SEA
  NEEDS TOURISM AND MONEY.

00:36:55.814 --> 00:36:59.017
WE NEED PEOPLE TO COME IN
  AND FILL UP THE RESTAURANTS

00:36:59.084 --> 00:37:01.352
AND PUT THEIR WAITRESSES
  TO WORK.

00:37:01.419 --> 00:37:04.155
AND I HOPE THAT,
 IN YEARS TO COME,

00:37:04.222 --> 00:37:06.825
THIS THING WILL TURN
 INTO A TOURIST ATTRACTION,

00:37:06.891 --> 00:37:10.028
AND BRING MILLIONS AND MILLIONS
 OF DOLLARS INTO CALIFORNIA.

00:37:21.673 --> 00:37:23.441
Clark Bloom:
 THE SALTON SEA REFUGE,
 IN PARTICULAR,

00:37:23.508 --> 00:37:26.444
WAS SET UP
 AS A WATERFOWL WINTERING AREA,

00:37:26.511 --> 00:37:30.615
THAT WAS OUR MAIN GOAL,
 BUT THINGS HAVE CHANGED A LOT.

00:37:30.682 --> 00:37:32.183
( White Noise )

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:34.385
(* Foreboding Music )

00:37:37.989 --> 00:37:39.557
Male Newscaster 1:
  ON MONDAY,
 BIOLOGISTS DISCOVERED

00:37:39.624 --> 00:37:41.826
58 DEAD BIRDS
  AT THE SALTON SEA,

00:37:41.893 --> 00:37:43.695
AND RESCUED 10 BROWN PELICANS.

00:37:43.762 --> 00:37:45.263
Male Newscaster 2:
 A MYSTERIOUS OUTBREAK
  OF AVIAN BOTULISM,

00:37:45.330 --> 00:37:48.600
A DEADLY ILLNESS FROM BACTERIA
  USUALLY FOUND IN MAGGOTS.

00:37:48.666 --> 00:37:49.968
Clark Bloom:
 WATER TEMPERATURES REMAIN HIGH,

00:37:50.034 --> 00:37:52.170
EVERYTHING IS IDEAL
 FOR BOTULISM,

00:37:52.237 --> 00:37:54.272
AND IT USUALLY DOES ITS THING.

00:37:54.339 --> 00:37:55.640
Male Newscaster 3:
  FOR THE PAST THREE WEEKS,

00:37:55.707 --> 00:37:56.608
EXPERTS AND VOLUNTEERS
  HAVE BEEN RESCUING

00:37:56.674 --> 00:37:58.476
AS MANY BIRDS AS POSSIBLE,

00:37:58.543 --> 00:38:02.413
INCLUDING THE RARE
  CALIFORNIA BROWN PELICAN.

00:38:02.480 --> 00:38:04.983
I GUESS I COULD
 BEST DESCRIBE '96--

00:38:05.049 --> 00:38:08.620
YOU HAD BIRDS
GETTING SICK AND DYING

00:38:08.686 --> 00:38:11.489
LITERALLY BY THE HUNDREDS
 ON A DAILY BASIS.

00:38:11.556 --> 00:38:13.124
THAT MIGHT HAVE BEEN
 AN INDICATION

00:38:13.191 --> 00:38:16.427
THAT THE SEA
  WAS NOT DOING WELL,

00:38:16.494 --> 00:38:19.931
THAT THERE WAS,
  ECOLOGICALLY, A PROBLEM.

00:38:19.998 --> 00:38:23.568
THE NUMBER OF DEAD BIRDS
 BUILT UP TO THE POINT WHERE--

00:38:23.635 --> 00:38:26.371
AT THAT TIME, WE ONLY HAD
  THE ONE INCINERATOR,

00:38:26.437 --> 00:38:27.972
WHICH IS THE SMALLER ONE,

00:38:28.039 --> 00:38:30.041
IT COULD NOT EVEN BEGIN
  TO TAKE CARE OF THE PROBLEM,

00:38:30.108 --> 00:38:33.244
IT RAN 24 HOURS A DAY,
  NONSTOP.

00:38:33.311 --> 00:38:34.646
( Fire Crackling )

00:38:34.712 --> 00:38:37.682
IT'S DEPRESSING,
 IT'S VERY DEPRESSING,

00:38:37.749 --> 00:38:39.250
MAINLY BECAUSE YOU KNOW

00:38:39.317 --> 00:38:41.386
THAT THERE'S NOTHING
  THAT YOU CAN DO,

00:38:41.452 --> 00:38:43.988
OTHER THAN TRY
 TO CLEAN THE MESS UP,

00:38:44.055 --> 00:38:45.056
TO MAKE IT STOP.

00:38:45.123 --> 00:38:48.092
WHEN YOU HAVE REALLY HOT DAYS

00:38:48.159 --> 00:38:49.694
WITH A VERY HIGH
 SALINITY LEVEL,

00:38:49.761 --> 00:38:52.897
IT SETS THE TABLE
  FOR BOTULISM TO GO CRAZY.

00:38:52.964 --> 00:38:57.001
THE TILAPIA PICK UP BOTULISM
  AND CARRY IT IN THEIR BODY.

00:38:57.068 --> 00:38:59.470
THE FISH BECOME TOXIC
  TO THE PELICANS,

00:38:59.537 --> 00:39:02.006
AND THEY GET BOTULISM AND DIE.

00:39:03.441 --> 00:39:09.614
BOTULISM SPREADS
 THROUGH CONTAMINATION

00:39:09.681 --> 00:39:11.216
OF OTHER BIRDS.

00:39:11.282 --> 00:39:13.051
WHEN A DEAD BIRD
  THAT HAS BOTULISM

00:39:13.117 --> 00:39:14.419
BEGINS TO DECOMPOSE,

00:39:14.485 --> 00:39:16.588
OF COURSE,
  IT FILLS UP WITH MAGGOTS.

00:39:16.654 --> 00:39:19.224
THE MAGGOTS PICK UP
  THE BOTULISM TOXIN,

00:39:19.290 --> 00:39:21.092
AND IT DOES NOT AFFECT THEM.

00:39:21.159 --> 00:39:24.062
SO EACH MAGGOT
 THAT CRAWLS AROUND,

00:39:24.128 --> 00:39:28.433
PRESENTS THE POSSIBILITY
 OF ANOTHER DEAD OR SICK BIRD.

00:39:28.499 --> 00:39:29.968
IT SPREADS QUITE FAST

00:39:30.034 --> 00:39:33.304
IF YOU DON'T DO ANYTHING
 TO TAKE CARE OF THE PROBLEM.

00:39:33.371 --> 00:39:34.606
CLEANING UP THE AREA

00:39:34.672 --> 00:39:38.576
IS ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT
THINGS THAT YOU CAN DO.

00:39:38.643 --> 00:39:41.613
YEAR-ROUND WE WILL GO OUT,
 ONCE A WEEK OR SO,

00:39:41.679 --> 00:39:44.382
AND COVER ONE PARTICULAR AREA
OF THE SEA OR ANOTHER,

00:39:44.449 --> 00:39:46.985
AND ONCE WE START
 PICKING UP PELICANS,

00:39:47.051 --> 00:39:48.586
USUALLY OUT OF
 THE SOUTH END HERE

00:39:48.653 --> 00:39:50.822
AROUND THE ALAMO RIVER
 OR THE NEW RIVER,

00:39:50.889 --> 00:39:54.092
THEN WE'LL STEP UP PATROLS,

00:39:54.158 --> 00:39:58.563
TO EVENTUALLY
  TO 7 DAYS A WEEK.

00:39:58.630 --> 00:40:00.098
SO WE'LL GO OUT THERE,

00:40:00.164 --> 00:40:01.432
WE'LL PICK UP THE BIRDS
  OFF OF THE SHORE

00:40:01.499 --> 00:40:02.867
THAT ARE DEAD.

00:40:02.934 --> 00:40:05.904
WE'LL ALSO PICK UP
 AS MANY LIVE BIRDS AS WE CAN,

00:40:05.970 --> 00:40:09.974
TREATING THEM ON-SITE
 AT OUR REHAB HOSPITAL.

00:40:10.041 --> 00:40:11.042
IT WAS KIND OF DIFFICULT
  AT FIRST,

00:40:11.109 --> 00:40:12.610
PICKING UP ALL THOSE PELICANS,

00:40:12.677 --> 00:40:15.546
AND KNOWING THAT THEY'RE SICK
  AND POSSIBLY COULD DIE,

00:40:15.613 --> 00:40:19.183
BUT NOW KNOWING
 THAT 7 OUT OF EVERY 10

00:40:19.250 --> 00:40:21.486
ARE GOING TO MAKE IT,

00:40:21.552 --> 00:40:23.288
YOU KNOW, IT KIND OF GIVES YOU
  A GOOD FEELING.

00:40:26.024 --> 00:40:28.459
THERE IS JUST
 A TREMENDOUS AMOUNT OF BIRDS

00:40:28.526 --> 00:40:30.628
THAT COME THROUGH THIS AREA,

00:40:30.695 --> 00:40:33.631
SIMPLY BECAUSE
  OF ITS GEOGRAPHIC LOCATION,

00:40:33.698 --> 00:40:36.034
PLUS THE MILD WINTERS.

00:40:36.100 --> 00:40:40.405
AND YOU ALSO HAVE TO REMEMBER
  THAT MOST OF THE--

00:40:40.471 --> 00:40:42.340
CALIFORNIA'S WETLANDS
 HAVE BEEN LOST

00:40:42.407 --> 00:40:43.908
FOR ONE REASON OR ANOTHER

00:40:43.975 --> 00:40:48.012
AND THIS IS ONE OF THE FEW
 REMAINING WETLANDS THERE ARE.

00:40:49.781 --> 00:40:52.984
WE STILL HAVE DISEASE PROBLEMS
 IN THE SUMMERTIME,

00:40:53.051 --> 00:40:55.853
WE HAVE HAD
EVERY SUMMER SINCE '96.

00:40:55.920 --> 00:40:59.057
I MEAN, IT'S, AGAIN,
PROBABLY NOT GOING TO GO AWAY.

00:40:59.123 --> 00:41:02.293
BUT BECAUSE OF OUR EXPERIENCE

00:41:02.360 --> 00:41:05.563
AND THE INFRASTRUCTURE
  THAT WE NOW HAVE,

00:41:05.630 --> 00:41:07.265
THESE PROBLEMS
  AREN'T REALLY BAD.

00:41:07.332 --> 00:41:09.434
WE ARE ABLE TO KEEP UP WITH IT,

00:41:09.500 --> 00:41:11.269
AND ACTUALLY
  STAY AHEAD OF THE GAME.

00:41:19.243 --> 00:41:21.245
(* Acoustic Guitar )

00:41:25.116 --> 00:41:26.250
THERE ARE A NUMBER OF PLANS

00:41:26.317 --> 00:41:28.353
TO ADDRESS THE PROBLEMS
 WITH THE SALTON SEA.

00:41:28.419 --> 00:41:30.788
AND THERE ARE DOZENS
 AND DOZENS OF PLANS

00:41:30.855 --> 00:41:32.223
TO ADDRESS THE PROBLEMS
 WITH THE SALTON SEA,

00:41:32.290 --> 00:41:34.926
AND PERHAPS
 THAT'S A PROBLEM IN ITSELF.

00:41:34.993 --> 00:41:37.395
IN MY MIND IT'S A CANAL,
  OR IT'S A PIPELINE,

00:41:37.462 --> 00:41:38.763
A WATER MOVEMENT:

00:41:38.830 --> 00:41:40.865
TAKE WATER OUT,
  PUT WATER BACK IN.

00:41:40.932 --> 00:41:42.300
THERE ARE OTHER APPROACHES

00:41:42.367 --> 00:41:43.735
TO LOOK AT PONDING PORTIONS
  OF THE SALTON SEA;

00:41:43.801 --> 00:41:45.069
TO DRAW THE SALT OUT;

00:41:45.136 --> 00:41:47.238
TO USE ENHANCED
  EVAPORATIVE SYSTEMS

00:41:47.305 --> 00:41:48.272
CURRENTLY
  USED IN ISRAEL.

00:41:48.339 --> 00:41:50.408
IT'S AN AGE-OLD PROBLEM,

00:41:50.475 --> 00:41:53.244
IT'S BEEN GOING ON FOR 30 YEARS.

00:41:53.311 --> 00:41:54.712
BUT IT'S COME TO THE POINT

00:41:54.779 --> 00:41:57.248
WHERE I REALLY DON'T THINK
THAT WE HAVE ANOTHER 30 YEARS.

00:41:57.315 --> 00:41:58.683
WE NEED TO SOLVE IT NOW.

00:42:00.785 --> 00:42:03.054
John Waters:
  SCIENTISTS KNEW
  HOW TO SAVE THE SEA,

00:42:03.121 --> 00:42:04.956
BUT THEY LACKED
  THE ATTENTION AND FUNDS

00:42:05.023 --> 00:42:06.357
TO MAKE IT HAPPEN.

00:42:06.424 --> 00:42:08.326
WHAT THEY NEEDED WAS A HERO,

00:42:08.393 --> 00:42:10.995
WHAT THEY GOT,
  WAS A ROCK STAR!

00:42:11.062 --> 00:42:16.167
* WITHOUT LOVE,
 WHERE WOULD YOU BE NOW? *

00:42:16.234 --> 00:42:18.169
* NOW, NOW, NOW...

00:42:18.236 --> 00:42:21.839
John Waters:
  SONNY BONO--
  MUSICIAN, RESTAURATEUR,

00:42:21.906 --> 00:42:24.876
PALM SPRINGS MAYOR,
  AND EX-HUSBAND OF CHER--

00:42:24.942 --> 00:42:26.744
WAS ELECTED TO CONGRESS,

00:42:26.811 --> 00:42:30.515
AND THE SALTON SEA
  FOUND ITS CHAMPION.

00:42:30.581 --> 00:42:34.218
I MAY HAVE TO WEAR
 THAT "SONNY AND CHER" THING

00:42:34.285 --> 00:42:35.820
FOR A WHILE,

00:42:35.887 --> 00:42:38.156
BUT I'LL OVERCOME THAT.

00:42:38.222 --> 00:42:41.726
I JUST NEED TO TALK TO PEOPLE
AND I'LL OVERCOME THAT.

00:42:41.793 --> 00:42:44.328
SONNY BONO WAS ABLE
TO DEVELOP AND GENERATE

00:42:44.395 --> 00:42:45.830
A LOT OF INTEREST
 IN THE SALTON SEA

00:42:45.897 --> 00:42:47.432
WITH HIS PEERS IN CONGRESS

00:42:47.498 --> 00:42:49.367
AND I THINK HE'S THE ONE
 THAT REALLY BROUGHT ATTENTION

00:42:49.434 --> 00:42:50.735
TO THE PROBLEMS
  OF THE SALTON SEA

00:42:50.802 --> 00:42:53.037
TO CONGRESS,
  TO THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT.

00:42:53.104 --> 00:42:56.074
Sonny Bono:
  IT'S THE FIRST TIME
 I'VE SEEN THIS KIND OF ENERGY

00:42:56.140 --> 00:42:59.644
GO INTO A PROJECT
 THAT IS DEARLY NEEDED

00:42:59.710 --> 00:43:03.481
TO PREVENT
 AN ENVIRONMENTAL DISASTER.

00:43:03.548 --> 00:43:06.851
Clark Bloom:
  SONNY WAS A REBORN
  ENVIRONMENTALIST.

00:43:06.918 --> 00:43:09.520
HE DID HAVE QUITE AN INTEREST
  IN WILDLIFE,

00:43:09.587 --> 00:43:12.356
AND WANTED TO SEE
SOMETHING DONE.

00:43:12.423 --> 00:43:16.060
YOU COULD NOT ONLY AVOID
THIS DISASTER,

00:43:16.127 --> 00:43:20.098
BUT YOU COULD ALSO CREATE
 A RECREATIONAL MECCA.

00:43:20.164 --> 00:43:22.867
I THINK SONNY WAS GOOD
 FOR THE SEA.

00:43:22.934 --> 00:43:24.869
UNFORTUNATELY,
HE WENT SKIING.

00:43:30.942 --> 00:43:33.845
HE HAD INTRODUCED
SOME LEGISLATION INTO CONGRESS

00:43:33.911 --> 00:43:35.213
JUST BEFORE HE DIED.

00:43:35.279 --> 00:43:37.815
AND, UNFORTUNATELY--

00:43:37.882 --> 00:43:40.618
I MEAN, THAT IS A TERRIBLE WAY
TO HAVE TO GET SOMETHING PASSED

00:43:40.685 --> 00:43:42.887
IS TO HAVE SOMEBODY GET KILLED
IN AN ACCIDENT,

00:43:42.954 --> 00:43:46.124
BUT I THINK THAT WAS PROBABLY
 THE SPARK

00:43:46.190 --> 00:43:47.558
THAT GOT CONGRESS TO GO AHEAD

00:43:47.625 --> 00:43:51.095
AND COME FORWARD
  WITH SOME FUNDING.

00:43:51.162 --> 00:43:53.264
AS SONNY SAID,
 "THE BEAT GOES ON,"

00:43:53.331 --> 00:43:56.934
AND ALL OF HIS FRIENDS
 IN CONGRESS

00:43:57.001 --> 00:44:01.239
HAVE PICKED UP THE BALL
 THAT HE WAS CARRYING

00:44:01.305 --> 00:44:03.741
AND I THINK WE'LL TAKE IT
 ACROSS THE GOAL LINE.

00:44:03.808 --> 00:44:05.143
Female Newscaster:
  REFERENCES WERE MADE ALL DAY

00:44:05.209 --> 00:44:07.979
TO KEEPING
  SONNY BONO'S LEGACY ALIVE,

00:44:08.045 --> 00:44:10.181
AS FEDERAL, STATE
  AND LOCAL LEADERS

00:44:10.248 --> 00:44:13.217
DISCUSSED WAYS TO SAVE
  THE AILING SEA.

00:44:13.284 --> 00:44:15.786
THIS IS A GREAT NATURAL RESOURCE

00:44:15.853 --> 00:44:17.922
TO BE MANAGED AND NURTURED
AND RECLAIMED,

00:44:17.989 --> 00:44:23.794
AND WE WILL BE INTRODUCING,
WITH MARY'S PERMISSION,

00:44:23.861 --> 00:44:25.463
ON SONNY'S BIRTHDAY,

00:44:25.530 --> 00:44:29.167
THE SONNY BONO
SALTON SEA RESTORATION PROJECT.

00:44:29.233 --> 00:44:31.602
( Applause )

00:44:31.669 --> 00:44:33.504
WE WANT TO KEEP THE AREA
FOR THE THINGS

00:44:33.571 --> 00:44:34.972
LIKE SONNY BONO WANTED,

00:44:35.039 --> 00:44:39.243
LIKE BOATING AND FISHING
 AND WATER-SKIING.

00:44:39.310 --> 00:44:41.012
AND WE WANT TO HELP
 ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT,

00:44:41.078 --> 00:44:42.313
THE SPORTS FISHERY;

00:44:42.380 --> 00:44:43.781
AND THEN THE FINAL ONE IS

00:44:43.848 --> 00:44:46.050
WE WANT TO HELP
  THE MIGRATORY BIRD HABITAT.

00:44:46.117 --> 00:44:48.386
WE HAVE A LOT OF GROUPS
  THAT ARE WORKING WITH US,

00:44:48.452 --> 00:44:50.054
THAT ARE INTERESTED
  IN SAVING THE SEA.

00:44:50.121 --> 00:44:52.156
WE HAVE ALL THE WAY FROM
 IRRIGATORS AND DEVELOPERS

00:44:52.223 --> 00:44:54.158
AND CITIES, ALL THE WAY
 TO ENVIRONMENTALISTS.

00:44:54.225 --> 00:44:56.594
SO WE'VE GOT A NICE GROUP
 OF A LOT OF PEOPLE.

00:44:56.661 --> 00:44:57.962
AND THAT'S NICE,
THAT'S FUN TO DO THAT,

00:44:58.029 --> 00:45:00.665
BECAUSE MAYBE WE CAN
 ALL COME UP WITH AN ANSWER.

00:45:00.731 --> 00:45:02.533
THAT'S WHAT WE HOPE.
 THAT'S WHAT WE HOPE.

00:45:02.600 --> 00:45:05.770
(* Music )

00:45:11.676 --> 00:45:13.110
John Waters:
  WITH THE CREATION

00:45:13.177 --> 00:45:15.813
OF THE SALTON SEA
  RESTORATION ACT IN 1998,

00:45:15.880 --> 00:45:18.382
THE PEOPLE AROUND THE SEA
  WERE ALL DOLLED UP

00:45:18.449 --> 00:45:21.385
AND READY FOR THE POOL PARTY
  TO BEGIN.

00:45:21.452 --> 00:45:24.555
BUT WITH THE PASSING YEARS
 AND CONTINUED DELAYS,

00:45:24.622 --> 00:45:27.525
THEIR VISIONS
  OF A HAPPY, BRIGHT FUTURE

00:45:27.592 --> 00:45:29.327
HAD BEGUN TO FADE.

00:45:29.393 --> 00:45:32.196
IT NOW SEEMS
  EVEN THE BONO BOOM

00:45:32.263 --> 00:45:34.165
HAS GONE BUST.

00:45:40.605 --> 00:45:43.708
(* Electric Guitar )

00:45:48.212 --> 00:45:52.383
EVERYONE WAS GOING TO SAVE
THE SALTON SEA.

00:45:52.450 --> 00:45:56.954
WHEN THE HYPE ENDED,
SONNY'S BURIED,

00:45:57.021 --> 00:46:03.861
A PARK--A RESERVE
 WAS NAMED AFTER HIM,

00:46:03.928 --> 00:46:07.098
HALF A FREEWAY SOMEWHERE,

00:46:07.164 --> 00:46:10.001
ALL THOSE PEOPLE LEFT.

00:46:10.067 --> 00:46:12.336
WE'RE BACK TO SQUARE ONE
 BASICALLY.

00:46:12.403 --> 00:46:13.771
JUST A LITTLE MORE IMPULSE,

00:46:13.838 --> 00:46:17.008
BUT WE'RE BASICALLY
 BACK TO THE SAME PROBLEM.

00:46:19.310 --> 00:46:20.478
WE ALL FELT LIKE,

00:46:20.544 --> 00:46:22.480
ONCE THE SALTON SEA AUTHORITY
 WAS CREATED,

00:46:22.546 --> 00:46:27.451
THIS WOULD THE BEST,
PROBABLY FINAL EFFORT,

00:46:27.518 --> 00:46:29.220
AND THEY'VE DONE
 A BEAUTIFUL JOB.

00:46:29.287 --> 00:46:31.822
I DON'T KNOCK
THE SALTON SEA AUTHORITY AT ALL.

00:46:31.889 --> 00:46:33.858
THEY'VE JUST BEEN GIVEN
THEIR CRITERIA

00:46:33.924 --> 00:46:35.126
AND THEIR PARAMETERS

00:46:35.192 --> 00:46:37.862
AND BEEN TOLD WHAT TO DO
 BY CONGRESS,

00:46:37.928 --> 00:46:42.099
AND THEN YOU'VE GOT THE
 POLITICAL PRESSURE AGAINST IT.

00:46:42.166 --> 00:46:45.736
WHATEVER THEY TRY TO DO,
 IT'S JUST UP A ONE-WAY STREET.

00:47:44.161 --> 00:47:45.363
I THINK IT BETTER CHANGE,

00:47:45.429 --> 00:47:47.231
OTHERWISE THERE AIN'T GONNA BE
 NO FUTURE,

00:47:47.298 --> 00:47:49.400
AT LEAST NOT HERE.

00:47:49.467 --> 00:47:52.203
THIS PLACE HERE IS GOING.

00:47:52.269 --> 00:47:55.039
THE WATER'S RECEDING
RATHER RAPIDLY.

00:47:55.106 --> 00:47:57.274
LAST YEAR,
 THOSE ROCKS RIGHT THERE,

00:47:57.341 --> 00:47:59.443
WERE UNDERWATER.

00:47:59.510 --> 00:48:01.612
THE FISHING
  IS NOT WHAT IS USED TO BE.

00:48:01.679 --> 00:48:04.548
THE PARTYING
  IS NOT WHAT IS USED TO BE.

00:48:04.615 --> 00:48:06.283
AND PEOPLE ARE,
 YOU KNOW WHAT,

00:48:06.350 --> 00:48:08.552
THEY SELL OUT
 AND GET OUT.

00:48:08.619 --> 00:48:10.221
THEY DON'T COME BACK.

00:48:10.287 --> 00:48:12.556
THIS IS DARN-NEAR
 A GHOST TOWN.

00:48:14.392 --> 00:48:16.260
THERE ARE MANY PEOPLE,
 WHO LIKE ME,

00:48:16.327 --> 00:48:17.328
CAN'T AFFORD TO MOVE

00:48:17.395 --> 00:48:18.596
IN THE SENSE THAT,

00:48:18.662 --> 00:48:20.498
"WHAT I COULD GET
 OUT OF THIS HOUSE,

00:48:20.564 --> 00:48:23.734
WOULDN'T BUY
  ANYTHING ANYPLACE ELSE."

00:48:23.801 --> 00:48:26.804
SO, PEOPLE HAVE SETTLED IN,

00:48:26.871 --> 00:48:34.211
AND A LOT OF THEM
HAVE COME HERE TO DIE.

00:48:37.882 --> 00:48:40.484
THE WATER THAT COMES
 INTO THE SALTON SEA,

00:48:40.551 --> 00:48:43.154
IN GREAT PART,
COMES FROM AGRICULTURE.

00:48:43.220 --> 00:48:45.156
SO THIS WATER COMES
  FROM THE COLORADO RIVER,

00:48:45.222 --> 00:48:46.624
IS USED ON OUR CROPS,

00:48:46.690 --> 00:48:48.926
AND EVENTUALLY FINDS ITS WAY
  INTO THE SALTON SEA.

00:48:48.993 --> 00:48:50.895
THAT WATER IS ATTRACTIVE.

00:48:50.961 --> 00:48:52.263
MANY PEOPLE ARE SAYING,

00:48:52.329 --> 00:48:54.131
"WELL, LET'S RECYCLE THAT WATER
THAT GOES INTO THE SALTON SEA,

00:48:54.198 --> 00:48:55.866
AND USE IT
 FOR SOMETHING ELSE."

00:48:55.933 --> 00:48:57.401
SOME PEOPLE
IN THE WATER DISTRICTS

00:48:57.468 --> 00:48:59.770
HAVE FLAT OUT SAID--
 IN THE LOCAL NEWSPAPER--

00:48:59.837 --> 00:49:00.805
SAY THAT IT'S A WASTE OF WATER

00:49:00.871 --> 00:49:02.339
TO LET IT FLOW
 INTO THE SALTON SEA."

00:49:02.406 --> 00:49:03.974
SAN DIEGO
AND THE IMPERIAL VALLEY

00:49:04.041 --> 00:49:06.677
ARE WORKING
ON A WATER TRANSFER AGREEMENT.

00:49:06.744 --> 00:49:10.548
IF APPROVED, SAN DIEGO COUNTY
WOULD BUY COLORADO RIVER WATER

00:49:10.614 --> 00:49:12.850
FROM THE IMPERIAL
 IRRIGATION DISTRICT.

00:49:12.917 --> 00:49:14.118
THE COUNTY WILL RECEIVE

00:49:14.185 --> 00:49:16.587
UP TO 200,000 ACRE FEET
 OF WATER EVERY YEAR,

00:49:16.654 --> 00:49:18.789
FOR AT LEAST
  THE NEXT 40 YEARS.

00:49:18.856 --> 00:49:20.424
WE'RE IN THE BEST
 POSSIBLE POSITION

00:49:20.491 --> 00:49:23.861
IN TERMS OF THIS BEING
 A GOOD DEAL FOR SAN DIEGO

00:49:23.928 --> 00:49:25.162
NOT ONLY TODAY,

00:49:25.229 --> 00:49:27.798
BUT 10 AND 20 AND 30 YEARS
 FROM NOW.

00:49:27.865 --> 00:49:31.035
I'M GETTING CYNICAL
 AND I'M GETTING VOCAL

00:49:31.101 --> 00:49:33.737
AND I'M TELLING PEOPLE,
 "THEY'RE STEALING IT!

00:49:33.804 --> 00:49:37.775
LIKE WAKE UP! WAKE UP!"

00:49:37.842 --> 00:49:41.779
THEY HAVE ABSOLUTELY CUT OFF
 EVERY SOURCE OF WATER

00:49:41.846 --> 00:49:43.681
THAT WILL MAINTAIN THIS.

00:49:43.747 --> 00:49:45.983
WE'RE DOWN
  TO ANNUAL RAINFALL.

00:49:48.786 --> 00:49:51.856
IT IS AN IDEAL, PERFECT SEWER.

00:49:51.922 --> 00:49:54.425
PUT IT IN THAT PERSPECTIVE,
  USE IT THAT WAY,

00:49:54.492 --> 00:49:56.961
AND THEN,
  THE WHOLE WORLD IS HAPPY.

00:49:57.027 --> 00:49:59.196
GO IN THERE,
 KILL ALL THE CRUMMY FISH OFF,

00:49:59.263 --> 00:50:01.499
TELL PEOPLE TO QUIT SWIMMING
 IN IT.

00:50:01.565 --> 00:50:05.202
IF YOU KILL ALL THE FISH OFF,
THE BIRDS WILL GO AWAY.

00:50:05.269 --> 00:50:07.271
WELL, THEN THE BIRDS
 AREN'T DYING ANYMORE,

00:50:07.338 --> 00:50:10.241
SO THE BIRD LOVERS
 ARE HAPPY.

00:50:10.307 --> 00:50:12.776
THE BIRDS--THEY'LL JUST GO
SOMEPLACE ELSE.

00:50:12.843 --> 00:50:14.345
THE PROBLEM IS,

00:50:14.411 --> 00:50:17.548
IS THAT WE HAVE,
IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA,

00:50:17.615 --> 00:50:19.950
CONSUMED 90% OF OUR WETLANDS

00:50:20.017 --> 00:50:21.685
IN THE TIME THAT
  THE SALTON SEA HAS EXISTED,

00:50:21.752 --> 00:50:22.853
SO THE SALTON SEA
 HAS COME TO BE

00:50:22.920 --> 00:50:25.189
A REPLACEMENT
  FOR THE WETLANDS

00:50:25.256 --> 00:50:26.457
FOR THESE BIRDS.

00:50:26.524 --> 00:50:29.860
SO NOW,
 AS THE SEA BECOMES SALTIER,

00:50:29.927 --> 00:50:32.763
AND THE FISH WILL NO LONGER
  BE ABLE TO SURVIVE,

00:50:32.830 --> 00:50:34.665
THE FISH-EATING BIRDS
  THAT COME HERE,

00:50:34.732 --> 00:50:36.166
WELL, THEY'LL HAVE TO GO
  SOMEWHERE ELSE.

00:50:36.233 --> 00:50:37.568
THE QUESTION IS,
  WHERE ARE THEY GOING TO GO?

00:50:37.635 --> 00:50:39.169
THEY CAN'T GO TO L.A.,
  BECAUSE WE'RE THERE.

00:50:39.236 --> 00:50:41.005
THEY CAN'T GO TO ORANGE COUNTY
  BECAUSE WE'RE THERE.

00:50:41.071 --> 00:50:42.172
SAN DIEGO, WE'RE THERE.

00:50:42.239 --> 00:50:44.875
THE COLORADO RIVER,
  WE'RE THERE.

00:50:48.112 --> 00:50:49.446
Norm Niver:
  PEOPLE SAY,

00:50:49.513 --> 00:50:52.016
"WHY SHOULD WE CARE
  IF THE SALTON SEA'S SAVED?"

00:50:52.082 --> 00:50:53.651
AND I SAY, "WELL,
 YOU'RE REALLY GONNA CARE

00:50:53.717 --> 00:50:58.722
"WHEN ABOUT 7 MILES
  OF THE NORTH END IS EXPOSED

00:50:58.789 --> 00:51:00.291
"AND THERE'S A LOT
  OF DRY BOTTOM THERE,

00:51:00.357 --> 00:51:04.028
"AND YOU GET A DOGGONE ALKALINE
  DUST STORM COME DOWN

00:51:04.094 --> 00:51:06.330
"AND SHUT THE WHOLE VALLEY
  DOWN

00:51:06.397 --> 00:51:09.400
IN A CLOUD OF ALKALINE DUST."

00:51:09.466 --> 00:51:12.636
WE'VE WARNED THEM AND STUFF.

00:51:12.703 --> 00:51:16.440
NO ONE CARES.

00:51:16.507 --> 00:51:18.709
THE STORMS
THAT RUN THROUGH HERE--

00:51:18.776 --> 00:51:23.113
WE'VE HAD AS HIGH AS 75 MILE
 AN HOUR WINDS NOTED HERE--

00:51:23.180 --> 00:51:25.282
RAISE DUST LIKE THEY DO
 UP IN THE OWENS LAKE,

00:51:25.349 --> 00:51:27.484
NORTH OF LOS ANGELES,

00:51:27.551 --> 00:51:31.989
WHICH THE METROPOLITAN
 DISTRICT OF LOS ANGELES CREATED

00:51:32.056 --> 00:51:34.024
BY THEIR BANKRUPTING
  THE OWENS LAKE FOR WATER.

00:51:34.091 --> 00:51:37.995
THE SAME WILL HAPPEN
  TO THE SEA IF IT DRIES UP.

00:51:41.498 --> 00:51:43.834
SAN DIEGO ONLY GIVE US
 $9 MILLION TOWARD MITIGATION

00:51:43.901 --> 00:51:47.204
TO FIX ALL THAT?

00:51:47.271 --> 00:51:48.939
I DON'T KNOW.

00:51:49.006 --> 00:51:51.875
NOW THESE PEOPLE
 THAT HAVE THE NICE HOMES

00:51:51.942 --> 00:51:57.815
IN INDIAN WELLS
 AND PALM SPRINGS AND--

00:51:57.881 --> 00:52:00.918
WE HAVE BEAUTIFUL GOLF COURSES
  IN PALM SPRINGS,

00:52:00.985 --> 00:52:02.419
YOU DON'T HEAR ANYBODY SAYING,

00:52:02.486 --> 00:52:04.355
"LET'S PUT SOME OF THE WATER
IN THE PALM SPRINGS GOLF COURSES

00:52:04.421 --> 00:52:05.756
INTO THE SALTON SEA."

00:52:05.823 --> 00:52:08.592
YOU'D PROBABLY HAVE A REBELLION!

00:52:08.659 --> 00:52:10.060
I THINK WHAT'S IMPORTANT
 FOR PEOPLE TO UNDERSTAND,

00:52:10.127 --> 00:52:11.428
THAT SMELL
THAT YOU DO SMELL OCCASIONALLY

00:52:11.495 --> 00:52:12.830
FROM THE SALTON SEA,

00:52:12.896 --> 00:52:14.965
AS IT GETS WORSE,
THAT SMELL WILL GET WORSE, TOO.

00:52:15.032 --> 00:52:18.402
PALM SPRINGS WILL HAVE NOTHING
  BUT THAT SMELL,

00:52:18.469 --> 00:52:19.403
WHERE SOME
 OF THE RICHEST PEOPLE

00:52:19.470 --> 00:52:22.206
IN THE UNITED STATES LIVE.

00:52:22.272 --> 00:52:23.507
WILL THEY KEEP

00:52:23.574 --> 00:52:25.509
THEIR MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR
  WINTER HOUSE

00:52:25.576 --> 00:52:26.877
AND GO GOLFING

00:52:26.944 --> 00:52:29.246
WITH GREEN FEES AT HUNDREDS
 OF DOLLARS EVERY DAY?

00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:33.450
NOTHING IS GOING TO HAPPEN
 WITH THE SALTON SEA

00:52:33.517 --> 00:52:35.586
UNTIL PEOPLE REALIZE
 THEY'RE GOING TO MAKE MONEY

00:52:35.653 --> 00:52:37.321
OR IT'S GOING TO HURT THEM
 IN THEIR POCKETBOOKS.

00:52:37.388 --> 00:52:39.890
THE FOLKS UP NORTH OF US
  HAVEN'T REALIZED

00:52:39.957 --> 00:52:42.493
THAT PALM SPRINGS
 WON'T BE PALM SPRINGS

00:52:42.559 --> 00:52:44.094
IF THE SALTON SEA FAILS.

